title: hernandez cider
directions: Stuff orange with cloves.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot and when liquid begins to simmer turn to low.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix soup, cooking wine and water until creamy and smooth. Pour evenly over the chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing on top and drizzle butter over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easy to make apple butter
directions: Core apples and slice, leaving skin on.
Cook overnight in slow cooker with apple cider or apple juice.
Separate pulp from skin.
Put pulp back in slow cooker with 2 cups sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and cook for 1 to 2 hours.
Cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well!
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: ham with cherry sauce
directions: Heat ham according to package instructions.
While ham is cooking, combine jelly, mustard, pineapple juice and wine in saucepan.
Cook and stir to boiling; simmer 3 minutes.
Thirty minutes before the end of heating time for the ham, remove it from the oven.
Score the fat in diamonds and pour 1/3 of the glaze over the ham.
Return to oven for remaining 30 minutes.
In saucepan with the remaining glaze, heat the cherry pie filling, raisins and pineapple to boiling, stirring occasionally.
At end of heating time, transfer ham to platter and spoon cherry sauce over the ham.
Pour remaining sauce into a bowl and pass at the table.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut ends off eggplant.
Slice in 1/2-inch circles.
Dip in water
and coat with BREADING MEAL.
Bake on sprayed cookie sheet at 350°
for
15 minutes, turn and bake 15 minutes more. Layer in pan
with
sauce
and
cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or serve
sliced
eggplant
with
sauce and cheese as toppings. Serves 4 to 6.

title: herb-marinated chicken(per serving: 170 calories and 7 g fat.)
directions: Skin chicken, if desired.
Rinse chicken.
Place in heavy plastic bag.
For marinade, in a bowl, combine wine, oil, vinegar, basil, oregano, onion salt and garlic.
Pour over chicken in bag. Close bag and turn to coat chicken well.
Marinate for 5 to 24 hours in refrigerator, turning bag occasionally.

title: poppy seed bread(quick)
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into 2 well greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: family favorite chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but add vegetables with seasoning packet. Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.

title: salad topping
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread over firm gelatin or use with fruit salads.
Store in refrigerator.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and extract.
Beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours (I usually chill overnight).
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: yummy yam bake
directions: Combine oats and milk; set aside.
Mash yams.
Stir in pineapple, brown sugar, egg, vanilla, oat mixture, nuts or marshmallows.
Blend very well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda together; add pineapple and eggs. Beat well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 sheet pan. Add brown sugar and nuts separately on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: alabama crab cakes
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent, set aside to cool. Gently combine all ingredients in bowl. Form into patties about 3/4 inch thick and 3 inches in diameter. Dust with small amount of crumbs. Fry in pan over medium heat, turning once. Serve hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Wash and drain shrimp; crumble.
Add to softened cream cheese. Add approximately 1 1/2 tablespoons Old Bay; adjust to taste. Form into ball and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Before serving, pour cocktail sauce over ball and serve with crackers. Note that refrigerating the shrimp ball will bring out the Old Bay seasoning; be careful not to over season.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.
Make 2 loaves of bread or one Bundt cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in greased pans.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: In a glass bowl, combine morsels and condensed milk. Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir until mixture is smooth. Add vanilla and walnuts. Stir until blended. Spread in foil lined 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm (about 2 hours).
Makes 1 1/4 pounds fudge.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake - pineapple
directions: Dump all ingredients into bowl and mix.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Place butter on top of mixture, then place second crust on top.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 375° until crust browns on top, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: southern breakfast casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions; set aside. Crumble sausage in a large skillet.
Add onion and pepper; cook over medium heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Combine grits, meat mixture and 1 cup cheese; spoon into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer, or until cheese melts.
Serves 8.
(Can freeze ahead, then heat.)

title: cucumber-dill sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve chilled with hot or cold fish, either broiled, steamed or baked.
Use with trout, salmon, sole, cod, whitefish, black sea bass, tuna, etc.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Cream together cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce. Drain and flake crabmeat; add to cheese mixture along with onions. Turn into greased 8-inch pie plate.
Top with slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple, tuna and rice salad
directions: Combine tuna, pineapple, rice, celery, olives and green peppers.
Chill.
Add salt and mayonnaise and mix lightly.
Serve on greens.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except blueberries, together, then stir in blueberries.
Bake in muffin tin at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: my special stew
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain.
Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion and all other condiments and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue to cook until vegetables are tender (20 to 30 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: garlic chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine melted butter, garlic powder, salt, pepper, thyme and onion salt. Mix well. Place the whole chicken in a baking pan and spread some of the garlic butter inside the chicken and then on the outside. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: shrimp arnaud
directions: Mix everything together, except shrimp.
Pour over shrimp and marinate in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all together.
Best if done early in day or a day ahead. Good with chips and vegetables.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up; cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until very chilled.
This can be made up to 2 days ahead.
Before serving, slice in 1-inch pieces and serve with salsa or sour cream.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all in a quart jar; mix well.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour; add butter and mix thoroughly.
If dough seems dry, work with harder.
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around.
Cover each olive; shape into ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: soft brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding the eggs, one at a time. Bake in greased
9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Check with toothpick to make sure they're done.

title: spinach and mushroom soup(easy; serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a saucepan over medium-high heat and uncovered, saute together onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is soft. Add thyme, parsley, chicken broth and chives. Stir to combine. Add spinach and cook for 5 minutes. Add cream and seasonings and heat through. Serve hot with a spoon of sour cream on top and a sprinkling of chives. If you don't have chives, the green part of green onions is fine. Can be prepared earlier and refrigerated. Reheat over low heat, stirring. Can be doubled or tripled.

title: poor man's dish
directions: Chop onion and brown with beef.
Add the beans.
Stir and heat together.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place apples in large bowl; cover with sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Blend shortening and eggs into apples.
Sift dry ingredients; stir only to mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together and shape in pan. Cook about 1 hour.

title: famous pumpernickel(recipe is for a 1 pound bread maker)
directions: Place all ingredients in bread pan and press start.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cooking oil and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add cinnamon and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and mix well again.
Stir in chopped nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Batter will be very stiff and hard to mix.
Spoon into a buttered and floured Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Check with a toothpick for doneness.
Baking depends on oven.

title: apple-carrot quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 or 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
In large mixing bowl, blend first 5 ingredients. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: avocado pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss pasta with dressing.
Add cheese, Prosciutto, black olives, onion, peas, broccoli, carrots, bell pepper, mushrooms, asparagus tips and sliced basil.
Toss gently. Season to taste.
Fan avocado slices on top.
Garnish with fresh basil leaves and tomato.
Serves 4.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Vary by omitting cocoa and add other ingredients, i.e. coconut, cherries, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
When done, cut into small pieces (discarding bones) and arrange chicken pieces in the bottom of a baking dish.
In layers, add cream of chicken soup, milk and Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Add broth from chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: mamie eisenhower's german chocolate candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk, and salt on low heat for 6 minutes.
Pour German chocolate, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Whip and butter. Beat well.
(I use electric mixer.)
Add vanilla and chopped nuts. Pour into large greased pan or drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup until it will spin a thread. Beat egg whites.
Add syrup slowly and beat until it begins to set.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: scrumptious zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini until tender. Saute carrots and onion in butter until limp.
Mix soup and sour cream. Add vegetables.
Pour into greased casserole.
Put bread crumbs in 1 tablespoon of butter and heat until coated.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zesty golden corn
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Blend in mustard.
Add onion and
mushrooms.
Cook,
stirring
constantly, over high heat until
tender-crisp (about 3 minutes).
Stir in corn and pepper, salt and parsley (if used).
Heat through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no bake - icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk over slow heat.
Crumble graham crackers in pan.
Then pour melted marshmallows over graham crackers.
Mix well with hands.
Add cherries, nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time until well blended.
Stir in almond and vanilla extracts.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixture using low speed.
Fold in sour cream and peaches.
Bake 75 to 85 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: You will need 1 Brown-in-Bag (10 x 16-inch).

title: biscuits
directions: In a dough pan, mix flour, shortening and milk.
Grease pan. Roll and cut out biscuits, being careful not to overwork dough. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 big biscuits.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Chill until set.

title: garden burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg white and bread crumbs.
(If using veal or beef, stir in 2 tablespoons water.)
Stir in carrot, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add Parmesan cheese and ground meat; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into four 3/4-inch patties.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick. Remove from fire.
Add peach Jell-O.
Cool.
Line baked and cooled pie shell with glaze.
Put in sliced peaches.
Add remaining glaze over the sliced peaches.

title: donna watson's lime cheesecake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers and melted oleo.
Pat in pan.
Beat Milnot until like whipped cream.
Then in another bowl mix
cream cheese and sugar.
Combine jello and boiling water and add to cream cheese mixture, then add to whipped Milnot.
Pour over graham crackers and refrigerate.

title: roast beef deluxe
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot overnight on high.
In the morning, add the 1 1/2 cups of water.
Before adding the vegetables, cook them 6 minutes in microwave.
When back from church, everything is ready.

title: angela's best bacon and eggs (candy)
directions: Melt white chocolate.
Place pretzels side by side on waxed paper (bacon).
Place about 1/2 teaspoon of melted chocolate in the center of the pretzels.
Top with a yellow M&M (yolk).
Repeat for as many candies as desired.
Let stand until chocolate is firm. Store in an airtight container.

title: easy dessert
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cornish hens with apple glaze
directions: Remove giblets from hens.
Rinse hens with cold water and pat dry.
Split each hen lengthwise using knife.
Place hens, cavity side up, on a rack in shallow roasting pan.

title: coconut supreme
directions: First Layer:
Blend softened oleo with flour. Add pecans and press into Pyrex dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs together. Add salt, baking soda and flour a little at a time. Fold in sour cream. Pour into two loaf pans. Bake in a 325 degree oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and ground beef in oil; drain.
Add steak sauce, catsup, parsley flakes, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni; drain and add to meat sauce.
Pour into greased dish; cover with mushroom soup.
Add shredded cheese to the top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Mix eggs and milk and add to flour mixture.
Fold in apples.
Put batter in greased muffin tins and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mix. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding mix well.
Make a well.
Add milk, oil and water.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix on medium speed until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°; let cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O.
Cool.
Stir pineapple, nuts, yogurt and pie filling.
Set aside to chill.
Combine cream cheese with sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread over set Jell-O mixture.
Top with nuts, chopped fine.
Refrigerate until topping is well set.
Put in large cake pan.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine vegetables, seasonings and milk in a 2-quart microwavable casserole; cover.
Microwave at High for 7 minutes, stirring once after 4 minutes.
Stir in beans and cheese. Microwave at High for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir halfway through cooking and again before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped popcorn in brown grocery bag.
Cook the brown sugar and Karo syrup for 2 minutes on High, then add the baking soda. Stir until bubbly.
Pour syrup over popcorn; shake to mix.
Put brown bag in microwave oven; microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag; microwave again for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour onto cookie sheet to cool.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake potatoes (60 to 75 minutes).
Cut a thin wedge from each potato and scoop out inside, leaving a thin shell.
In large mixer place potato insides and all ingredients. Beat at medium speed until fluffy (2 to 3 minutes).
Fill shells with potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place on cookie rack. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: favorite christmas or easter casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cut in large pieces.
Cut eggs and cheese in large pieces.
Season white sauce with marjoram, pepper, few drops of Worcestershire.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; add cubed bread.
Spread grated cheese over bread.
Cook sausage; separate chunks.
Drain all grease from meat and spread over cheese.
Add 2 cups milk to beaten eggs; pour over meat.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Mix 1/4 cup milk with soup and pour over casserole. Bake at 325° for 60
minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix powdered milk, honey and peanut butter in a pan.
Stir until ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Roll out in long rolls. Spread coconut and cereal on wax paper.
Roll the long rolls in cereal mixture.
Cut in pieces and chill.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft, add garlic and cook 1 minute. Add water and the rest of ingredients, except pasta. Bring to a boil. Cook 30 minutes on simmer covered.
Cook pasta in a separate pot and then add to lentils.

title: spaghetti salad(with mccormick salad supreme)
directions: Mix spaghetti ("I have found it mixes better if the spaghetti is cut in smaller pieces instead of leaving it long), green pepper, onion, tomato, dressing, salad seasoning, pepperoni and celery and let set overnight or at least several hours before serving.
Mix well again before serving.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: Stir together turkey, soups, stuffing, eggs, margarine and broth.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Spread buttered crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into meat loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.
Should be golden brown on top.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix. Add can of peaches; pour over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Don't drain juice off peaches, use.

title: rippled cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Jab holes in cake with large fork over entire top of cake.
Prepare gelatin according to directions and pour over top of cake.
Chill cake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: english muffin appetizer
directions: Spread mayonnaise on English muffins.
Add cheese, then cut up onions. Sprinkle capers on top of each.
Put in microwave oven or broiler until cheese is melted. Cut in quarters.
Serve warm.

title: black rock baked oatmeal
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice for sushi
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, salt and 1/4 cup of the sugar into a large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in yeast mixture, eggs, sour cream and vanilla to make a smooth dough; form into a ball.
Seal in plastic.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Divide dough in half; wrap and return half to refrigerator.
Roll on a lightly floured board to 12 x 18-inches.
Fold in thirds.
Roll out again on floured board to same size, repeat folding.
Repeat process 1 more time; cut in half to form two 6-inch squares.
Turn in corners to form circle.
Sprinkle board with about 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Roll out to a 12-inch circle.
Cut in 8 wedges.
Roll up each wedge and place on greased baking sheet. Repeat until all is rolled.
Let rolls rise until puffy (about 45 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown. Makes 32 crescents.

title: cherry squares
directions: Blend till crumbly, press half of mixture into a 9-in. square pan.

title: lu's holiday asparagus
directions: To Mix:
Drain asparagus.
Set aside.
Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Set aside. Layer one-half of asparagus, water chestnuts, mushrooms, pimento, egg and soup mixture in an oblong, greased casserole dish.
Repeat layers; cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice. Mix well. Beat egg yolks. Add to cornstarch mixture.
Add water. Bring mixture just to boiling point over medium heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add margarine and grated lemon rind to thickened mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Prepare egg white meringue.
Beat 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar. Spread on pie and bake 8 minutes until brown.

title: peach sauce
directions: Combine peaches and enough juice in a saucepan.

Bring to a boil over medium heat; cover, reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 to 10 minutes, or until peach slices are tender. Spoon mixture into container of an electric blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Return mix to saucepan; add sugar and remaining ingredients to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes until thickened.
Serve warm over pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: sweet-n-sour slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard, celery seed, pepper and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Chop cabbage, onion, carrots and bell pepper.
Alternate layers in large container.
Pour cooled mixture over cabbage layers.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet or wok.
Add peppers, carrots and garlic; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce; add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar and ginger.
Bring to a full boil.

title: chocolate cream balls
directions: Divide into bowls and add flavorings:
vanilla, rum, mint, orange, cherry, lemon, etc.
Use food coloring to mix to appropriate color/flavor.
Add pecans or walnuts (chopped), etc. Chill balls.
Roll in melted chocolate.
Add 2 tablespoons paraffin to chocolate.
This equals glazed professional appearance.

title: tanta baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place dry ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend about one minute, stopping occasionally to stir. Coat chicken pieces with oat mixture; dip into milk.
Coat again with oat mixture.
Place in a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; drizzle with margarine.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with fork.

title: won't last cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one pan.
Put nuts in last. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: easy as pie peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9x13 inch baking dish.
Mix together juice from peaches, flour, sugar, and egg. Pour mixture evenly over margarine.
Layer sliced peaches across top of mixture without stirring.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy tuna rice with peas
directions: Bring peas, water, soup, tuna and bouillon cube to a full boil in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: zucchini casserole pie
directions: Butter large, deep pie pan.
Stir everything together and pour into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
This is very good.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pie filling and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into long dish or pan (2-quart).
Add bananas when set; spread with Cool Whip.

title: low-fat banana cream pie
directions: Make graham crust with melted butter and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Beat instant pudding with milk.
Slice bananas thin onto graham crust.
Pour banana pudding over.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: winter's day soup
directions: Brown the ground beef in a large pot and don't drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 1/2 hours or all day.
Add extra water, if necessary.

title: macaroni and cheese(healthy heart)
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish sprayed with vegetable spray, layer macaroni and cheeses, topping with cheese.
In a small bowl, mix melted margarine, flour, mustard, red and black pepper, salt and skim milk.
Blend and pour over macaroni and cheese mixture. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven and bake until cheese on top begins to brown.
Serves 8.
Contains 223 calories and 25% fat.

title: granny horton's old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Mix molasses, margarine, sugar and egg.
Beat well.
Combine spices, soda and flour, then add to molasses mixture.
Mix. Chill.
Roll in 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet two inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: In large saucepan, combine egg yolks, water, vinegar and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and reaches 160°.
Remove from heat.
Fold in whipped cream.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add dressing and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line pie plate with crust and trim.
Mix apples, sugar, flour, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and lemon juice. Put in pie.
Dot with butter.
Put top crust onto pie.
Cut patterns in top crust.
Bake 40 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
Cook over low to medium heat for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, add sugar, blend in peanut butter then pour in milk.
Fold in topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: meaty-cheesy dip
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef until crumbly and done.
Add cheese and picante sauce.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips and jalapeno peppers.

title: sausage and zucchini stir-fry
directions: Slice sausage in 1/4-inch slices.
Brown in wok or large skillet.
Add onions when sausage is nearly done.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, lemon juice, salt, Tabasco sauce and oregano. Cook uncovered for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with crusty Italian bread.

title: dromedary pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased, floured pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape beef mixture into loaf or pack mixture into loaf dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Stir, by hand or mixer all ingredients except eggs and butter.
Stir eggs lightly and add slightly cooled melted butter. Add gently to pumpkin mixture.

title: cheese and sausage appetizers
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix on medium-low.
Stir in cooked sausage.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm or cold. Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter; add onions and garlic; cook until tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Pour into jar; cover and refrigerate.
Use for all meats.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges, pineapple and cherries.
Combine with apples, bananas, pie filling and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Chill until serving time.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and cheese.
Add sausage and mix.
Roll into small balls and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour juices, water and sugar into a 6 to 8 cup percolator.
In basket, add the cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks. Perk.

title: braised italian beef kabobs
directions: Alternately thread 3 beef cubes and 2 carrot slices on each of 9 to 12 skewers.
Combine onion soup mix and flour.
Dredge kabobs in mixture, reserving remaining
mixture.

title: rich chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate bits and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Check after 45 minutes (toothpick test).
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice onions and cabbage.
Brown both in oleo.
Cook until tender.
Add flour, broth and sherry.
Simmer.
Slice bread in 3/4-inch slices.
Toast slices in jelly roll pan at 450°.
Place toast on soup in oven-safe bowls.
Sprinkle cheese over bread. Place bowls on pan in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Servings:

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken, onions, cheese, garlic salt and chili powder together and add tomatoes.
Soften the tortillas in the warm chicken stock.
Line baking dish with the tortillas and pour chicken mixture over the tortillas.
Pour the soup over the chicken and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatine in clam juice. Do not boil.
Put remaining ingredients except sour cream in a food processor.
Add the gelatine mixture.
(Be sure any bones in salmon have been removed.)
Blend until smooth. Add sour cream and blend for a moment until well mixed.
Pour into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Excellent for luncheon or a first course.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken; save 1 cup of broth.
Mix chicken broth, eggs and celery soup.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine well.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello and concentrates and juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Cook apples for about 45 minutes.
Add dash of salt and stick of margarine to well drained apples.
Add Sweet 'N Low and cool. Add well beaten eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Put in uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Use 1 1/2-inch muffin or tart pan.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in a frying pan.
Remove from pan.
Melt oleo.
Add milk slowly.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Alternate potatoes, onions, cream sauce and pork chops in a greased casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until tender.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and onion.
Drain well.
In a bowl mix spinach and onion, bread crumbs and cheese.
Stir in eggs and margarine. Shape into 1-inch balls, then place on lightly greased cookie sheet (can be frozen at this time for later use).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch to make sure they don't burn.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in large pot; add onion, chili mix, beans and tomato sauce.
Add 6 cups water and simmer for 1 hour on low heat or until cooked.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: In large skillet saute onion in oil until tender.
Add catsup, water, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and chili powder.
Bring to boil.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Turn pieces occasionally.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes or longer until tender.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon	juice
over
mashed bananas and combine all ingredients.
Pour in molds and freeze.
Remove from molds and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square baking pan with plastic wrap.
In 3-quart microwavable bowl, combine corn syrup and evaporated milk.
Stir until well blended.
Microwave on High (100%) 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in sugar, vanilla and walnuts. With wooden spoon, beat until thick and glossy.
Spread in prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Makes 25 squares.

title: carefree chicken casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, water and rice in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Top with onion soup mix.
Bake at 325 for two hours.
If short on time bake at 450° for 1 hour.
If rice seems dry during baking, more water may be added.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Place berries in unbaked pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over berries.
Bake slowly at 300° until firm.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light golden brown.
Let cool slightly and cut into small squares.
Best when served warm.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: easy chicken or turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli for 4 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Place poultry slices over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over poultry.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: red cabbage with wine
directions: Fry onion in butter 3 or 4 minutes.
Add cabbage and sprinkle with brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Then add wine and vinegar. Cover and cook slowly for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine all ingredients, except noodles, in a large pan.
Cook several hours on a slow simmer.
About 20 minutes before you eat, add the noodles.
Cook until done.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls evenly in cookie sheet and bake at 375° until brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing together and spread evenly over rolls.
Chop broccoli, peppers and carrots very fine and sprinkle over top.
Also, sprinkle both cheeses on top.
Refrigerate.
(Better after refrigerated.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all
ingredients;
cook
in a baking dish for 1 hour, or until chicken is done.
Bake at 350°.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar 1/2 cup at a time; cream until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with cream.	Add vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat with electric mixer 3 to 4 minutes.
Put into 2 floured bread tins.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops o'brien
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, heat oil; brown pork chops and drain.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in saucepan, margarine, shortening, cocoa and water and bring to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Bake in shallow greased pan (20 x 13-inch) at 375° for 20 minutes or until it springs back to touch.
Five minutes before cake is done, prepare frosting.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Spread applesauce on bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish or shallow glass baking dish.
Cover with cherry pie filling. Arrange fruit in layers atop pie filling.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top, then sherry.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, peppers and garlic.
Add bay leaves, thyme and parsley for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stock or water; bring to a boil.
Add choice of meat, rice and seasonings.
Cook 45 minutes.
Serve hot with French bread.

title: salsa
directions: Cook your hamburger meat and while doing that cook all the other ingredients in a slow cooker.
Then when meat is done add to the mix, let cook for about one hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften (real mushy).
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Refrigerate for about an hour.
Form into a ball and roll in either chopped nuts or cracker crumbs.

title: texas wiener sauce
directions: Saute onion and oleo.
Brown the beef slightly.
Simmer until thickened.
Chop onion and use raw with mustard for hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: sausage with pineapple and brown sugar(party foods)
directions: Combine in pan and lightly sprinkle with brown sugar.
Heat and serve warm with toothpicks.

title: beef dip
directions: Combine beef, mayonnaise, bell pepper, onion, dressing and cream cheese.

title: calico salad
directions: Mix peas, green beans, corn, celery and pimento.
Then boil sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over first mixture. Serve chilled.
This is better when prepared night before and refrigerated.

title: yummy cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir gently with a wooden spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch buttered baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together; spread in 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread 1 large container of Cool Whip over cooled crust.

title: buffet casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut beef in 2-inch strips.
Melt oleo; add mushrooms.
Saute and remove.
Add beef and brown.
Return mushrooms to skillet.
Add green beans, bouillon and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Mix flour with a little water to make paste.
Stir in liquid.
Cook until thickened.
Arrange ravioli around sides of an 8 x 10-inch pan. Spoon meat in center.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and water until clear and thick. Remove
from
heat
and add vanilla and butter.
Serve warm over ice cream.
May be stored in refrigerator and served cold.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring every few minutes to avoid sticking and scorching. When done, set aside to cool.
Store in fridge.
Makes 2 cups.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken on stove.
Cut into cubes and place in bottom of glass casserole dish.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers (enough to cover) and spread over mixture.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and pour over crackers.
Add poppy seed!
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: tuna bake
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Each serving equals 3 protein, 1 vegetable, 1 bread and 1/2 milk.

title: molasses crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine to form crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Add molasses and spices.
Mix with remaining 3 cups crumbs.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat.
Stir in everything else, except 1 cup of nuts.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
Fill and frost.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes and mix all ingredients togethe reserving 1/4 c. oleo and corn flakes.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and 1/4 c. oleo.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash the fresh mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems.
Place stems in small bowl with onion and butter.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mound in mushroom caps.
Arrange caps on paper towel lined plate with larger caps to the outside. Microwave 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, until heated, rotating plate once or twice.

title: olive dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with your favorite crackers, chips or veggies.

title: tomato and bacon cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients together and garnish with parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: venison chili
directions: Fry suet in heavy kettle.
Add venison.
Cook, stirring, until browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook slowly for 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally, adding water as needed for desired consistency.
Serve with pinto beans.
Freezes well.

title: delicious rolls
directions: Use enough flour to make dough (not too stiff).
Let rise once; punch down and let rise again.
Make into any type of rolls desired.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° to 400° until brown.
This is the best roll recipe I have found.

title: pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown chops in skillet. Mix remaining ingredients together. Layer chops in a baking dish and pour sauce over top. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chops are tender.

title: sauce for broiling fish or chicken
directions: Brush fish or chicken filet with sauce.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes.

title: hawaiian delight salad
directions: Mix tuna, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and parsley in another bowl.
Put contents into 2 bowls together.
Chill before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Serves 6.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix well and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray baking dish with cooking spray. Mix all ingredients and pour into dish. Dot surface with butter pieces. Bake 30 minutes or until center is firm.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine egg, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper until well blended.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Fold in salmon. Shape mixture into 4 patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Coat all sides with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with cocktail sauce, if desired.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using fork.
Mix together coffee and sugar, then drizzle over brownies.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, omitting chilling.

title: cheesy apple ham grill
directions: Mix apple, 1/3 cup of the dressing, walnuts and cloves.
For each sandwich, top 1 bread slice with 1 cheese slice, apple mixture, ham, second cheese slice and second bread slice.
Spread outside of sandwiches with remaining dressing.
Grill until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat on medium speed with mixer.
Add milk, peanut butter and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix slowly until well blended and smooth.
Place mixture into prepared crust and chill for several hours.

title: orange salad
directions: First mix pineapple and Jell-O together.
Then mix marshmallows, Cool Whip and cottage cheese with pineapple and Jell-O.
Refrigerate.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour with salt in a small mixing bowl.
Add oil and milk, both at once.
Stir with a fork until lightly mixed.
Dough should round up in a ball.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornbread mix and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
This makes enough for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spinach bread
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex baking dish.
In bowl, whisk together the flour, milk, eggs, salt and baking powder.
Stir in cheese and spinach.
Brown sausage and break into small pieces.
Drain excess fat by placing on paper towel.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
When serving leftovers, it is usually better when heated in microwave or oven. You can freeze small sections.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered dish and top with the following:

title: baked french fries
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oil on lipped cooking sheet.
Put diced or sliced potatoes on cooking sheet.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna tofu patties
directions: Squeeze water from tofu and crumble.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonful into greased frying pan.

title: aunt beth's cornbread
directions: Mix and beat well eggs, sour cream and oil.
Mix meal, baking powder and salt together, then add to first mixture.
Add 1 small can cream-style corn.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes in an 8-inch or 9-inch baking dish.

title: nubbies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter. Add vanilla and enough milk to make a thick batter; a spoon should stand up in the batter.
Add raisins.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool slightly and cut into squares. This is much like a scone.

title: eggplant
directions: Put water, salt, onion and eggplant in pressure cooker for 5 minutes of pressure.
Remove all ingredients from cooker and transfer to another pan or wok.
Cook in wok until water is dissolved.
While dissolving, add Ro-Tel tomatoes and salt to taste.
Add red pepper if needed, but tomatoes are quite spicy!

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onions together.
Spread in pie pan.
Spoon cocktail sauce on top of mixture.
Then spread crabmeat on top of cocktail sauce. Sprinkle parsley flakes on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp real fine and mix all together.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: soda-citrus fruit punch
directions: Partially
thaw juices, put in bowl, add chilled sodas, stir in	ice
and
garnish
with lime slices.
If punch is too tart may add
quart ice cream just before serving.
Serves 12.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
In food processor, combine chicken broth, cheese, flour, onion, garlic powder and sour cream.
Blend until smooth.
Pour sauce into saucepan and simmer until thick.
This is a fairly thin sauce and will thicken.

title: graham cracker taffy
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Layer graham crackers in a 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet. Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Put in refrigerator for 15 minutes and break into pieces.

title: hot antipasto
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add mashed bananas and nuts. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix dry jello and pineapple; add Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Mix well.
Chill.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and put marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Cool 1 hour and frost.

title: no side effect pancakes
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Butter
a large cookie sheet. Mix all the ingredients and pour batter evenly onto the cookie sheet. Bake about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with Cool Whip and chocolate shavings.

title: fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Do not stir after first mixing.
When ready, remove from stove and add margarine and vanilla, then add chips and marshmallows.
Beat until they are melted and mixture thickens. Add 1 cup nuts and spread on buttered pan.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Grease pan with butter and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: corn flake chicken
directions: Combine crushed corn flakes, Zesty Italian Dressing Mix, Parmesan and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken breasts in milk then the crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2 dish.
Bake 375° for 18 minutes.

title: carameled peanuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy; not stiff. Add peanuts and stir until they are well-coated. Combine sugar and salt. Pour this over the nuts and egg white mixture. Bake at 225° on a greased, tinfoil-lined cookie sheet. Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Add ingredients in order given and mix well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: company's coming meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup.
Form into a loaf.
Cover bottom of the baking dish with ketchup (about 1/2-inch deep). Place in preheated 350° oven, covered, and bake approximately 1 hour.
The ketchup and juices from the meat blend and make a great tomato sauce to serve over the meat loaf.

title: deer barbecue
directions: Cut deer meat in small chunks or pieces.
Cook in pressure cooker for approximately 30 minutes or in regular pot 1 1/2 hours until very tender.
Pour most of broth off.
Take a fork and pull apart meat until stringy.
Mix in barbecue sauce, one part regular to two parts hot and spicy.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes with lid on.
Add chopped onion, pepper and salt; cook on low heat, stirring often.

title: *chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Use ungreased tube pan.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Make a well and add the oil, egg yolks, almonds, water and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Put egg whites and cream of tartar in a large mixing bowl; beat until very stiff peaks form.
Pour egg yolk mixture over and fold in (this is an important step).
Do not stir.
Fold in coconut.

title: bill's corn casserole
directions: Blend together corn, Bisquick, egg, oil and milk.
Pour half the batter into greased 9 x 10-inch casserole.
Sprinkle about 1/2 the chiles and 1/2 the cheese on top.
Repeat batter, chiles and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lazy wife's dill pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise in slices.
Pack in jars with onion, 2 or 3 stalks of celery and dill.
Heat sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Pour over pickles.
Put lids and rings and place in a hot water bath until water cools.
Ready in 3 weeks.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon into boiling water or broth.
Let boil 15 minutes, do not cover.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and add peanut butter and sugars gradually.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating after every addition.
Drop mixture 1 teaspoon at a time 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with tines of fork until very thin. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauteed liver and onions
directions: I use a large cast-iron (8-inch) frying pan.
Saute onions in 4 tablespoons of margarine until tender.
Put onions in bowl; set aside.
Melt 4 remaining tablespoons of margarine in skillet.
Put half of flour in plastic bag; toss in liver, one piece at a time, shaking bag to coat well.
Saute liver in margarine until cooked to taste.
As each piece is done, place in bowl with onions.
When all of liver is cooked, dissolve bouillon in 2 cups hot water and set aside.
Thicken as you would any gravy with small amount of flour and bouillon hot water, until flour is used.
Once gravy is cooked, add sauteed liver and onions and heat through.
Add a few drops of Kitchen Bouquet.

title: yummy carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 10 minutes, put aside.
In large skillet mix honey, mustard, curry powder and lemon juice.
Add carrots, cook stirring 3 more minutes.

title: southern meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion, green pepper, celery, mushrooms and garlic in a large bowl, mixing well.
Add ground beef; mix just until blended.
Shape into an 8 x 4-inch loaf and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine catsup and water.
Spoon over loaf.
Bake an additional 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6 people.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Brown ribs on all sides in oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Place ribs in roaster or baking dish and pour enough barbecue sauce over ribs to cover them.
Cover roaster or baking dish and bake ribs at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in flour, broth and milk until thickens.
Mix chicken with vegetables.
Pour in baking dish. Cover with dough.
(May used canned biscuits.)

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Pound chicken breast to even thickness.
Combine all other ingredients in Ziploc plastic bag plus chicken.
Press out air and zip.
Refrigerate 3 to 24 hours.
Turn several times.
Drain chicken; reserve marinade.
Broil chicken on grill 5 to 7 minutes; baste with marinade.
Slice chicken in thin strips, put in tortillas.
Add toppings as wanted.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Remove from mixer and stir in boiling water.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: candied walnuts or pecans
directions: Blend water, sugar, and Karo.
Boil 3-4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, vanilla, and butter.
Stir until cream is blended.
Add nuts and spread quickly on waxed paper. Cool and break into chunks.

title: pat nixon's chestnut-apple dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make dressing.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: In a heavy small saucepan heat and stir 1/2 cup of the chocolate pieces over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Meanwhile, stir together flour and baking powder. In a small mixer bowl beat butter or margarine until softened. Add sugar and beat until well combined.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
On baked base, layer remaining chocolate pieces, nuts and marshmallows.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more or until marshmallows are golden.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large bowl about 30 seconds.
Blend in condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight (optional).
Garnish with lemon or lime.
Return leftover pie to freezer.

title: baked beans
directions: Pick over dry beans and put in 6 to 8-quart kettle.
Wash, drain and put back in kettle.
Add cold water to about 5-inches above beans.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain beans. Return to kettle and add water to cover.
As beans boil you will need to add more water.
Cook just until the skins on beans begin to pop and beans are slightly soft.
(It is very easy to overcook and you will have a very mushy, paste-like dish of beans.)
Drain again and put into roaster.

title: mocha truffle cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine and the 1/2 cup chocolate pieces over low heat.
stir in coffee crystals; cool 5 minutes. Stir in sugars, eggs and vanilla.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground meat; drain if needed. Add chili beans, water, taco seasoning and chili powder (if desired, add green pepper and onion).

Simmer 15 minutes. Put meat in tortillas and roll them up. Put into a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan. Add remaining meat and bean mixture on top. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water and set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks 1 at a time, beating after each.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in egg whites.
Gently stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round cake pans and bake at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well; chill 1 day ahead.
Use on all fresh vegetables.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Combine all and warm in crock-pot.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, 2 teaspoons of salt and oil to boil.
Add acini de pepe. Cook at rolling boil until done.
Drain, rinse with water, drain again and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and acini de pepe.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate until chilled in airtight container. Salad may be kept for as long as a week.
It also may be frozen, but the texture will be altered slightly.
Makes 25 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone it.
Cook rice along with celery and onion until rice is cooked.
Line casserole dish with chicken. Cook broccoli in boxes in microwave.
Mix broccoli and rest of ingredients together.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Make batter with flour, sugar and milk.
Pour batter over butter.
Place peaches evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple chutney
directions: Cut 1 Delicious apple into shreds.
Add 1 minced onion, moisten with vinegar and sprinkle with chopped parsley and chopped green chili.
Serve as a relish with curry, stews or pot roast.

title: lincoln's special
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and chili peppers.
Pepper and salt well.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Put in each tortilla some of the ground beef, 2 tablespoons refried beans, sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Roll tortillas up and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour salsa over to taste, then pour enchilada sauce all over it.

title: favorite clam chowder
directions: Cook salt pork in a heavy saucepan over moderate heat until crisp and brown.
Drain crisp pieces on paper.
Cook onion in fat until tender.
Add diced potatoes, salt and pepper and liquid drained from clams.
Add water, if necessary, just to cover potatoes; cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Add clams. Stir in the 2 cups milk and cream and set aside to "ripen" for 2 hours or longer.
Reheat slowly.
Stir flour and 2 tablespoons milk together to form a smooth paste.
Stir into chowder and cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Garnish each serving with crisp salt pork pieces.
Makes 4 meal size portions or 6 first course cups.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soak onions and cucumbers in salt water for 1 hour.
Drain and pack into canning jars as tightly as possible.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Pour liquid to fill each jar.
Cool and freeze.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Season shrimp with salt and red pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
When transparent, add shrimp and stir-fry until pink.
Add soup; mix up until soup is heated.
Mix with cooked rice.
Butter a baking dish and put mixture in; bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cele's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, peanut butter and sugars. Add egg, beat
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Mix well. Roll into walnut sized balls, then roll balls in mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Press with fork. Bake at 375° for about 7 - 8 minutes.

title: almond cassata
directions: Step 1:
Cut cake horizontally to make 3 equal layers.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes; add cream cheese and margarine or butter. Beat until melted.
Blend in sour cream. In separate bowl, combine eggs, milk, onions, salt and pepper.
Add to potato mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Put into greased casserole or 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Rough puree the artichokes, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in ovenproof dish and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers for dipping.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts or raisins and bananas. Bake at 325° in a 10-inch Bundt pan for 1 hour (or in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes).
Check about 10 minutes before the required time for baking is complete.

title: german sauerkraut casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole dish in the order given.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: taco pie
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Brown beef with taco sauce.
Spread potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour drained corn on potatoes, then add ground beef and spread evenly.
Add grated cheese and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp and beef jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven; saute green peppers, onions and garlic in oil until soft, but not browned. Add ground beef and cook until brown. Drain off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp and rice. Cover; heat to boiling. Simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and rice; simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon and set aside.
Add milk to reserved liquid to make 1 cup.
Saute onions in butter.
Combine salt, pepper, hot sauce and flour.
Add milk mixture and cook until thick.
Add salmon, lemon juice and corn flakes.
Shape into croquettes and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: easy german chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add margarine, coconut and pecans; mix well.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or make 24 tart shells and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer slowly together for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use to baste ribs when cooking.

title: amish funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients, then stir in egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Heat oil to 375° and pour batter into hot oil through a household funnel.
Control the flow by holding your finger over the bottom of the funnel.
Make patterns, designs and swirls with the stream of batter.
Cook until brown.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dilly new potatoes
directions: Scrape and cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until done. Combine other ingredients.
Pour over drained potatoes.
Heat 1 to 2 minutes, turning potatoes to coat with mixture.
Makes four servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, beating well. Stir in corn and milk.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir once halfway through cooking.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place chopped chicken in large bowl.
Add celery, pickles, green pepper, eggs and vinegar.
Add mayonnaise as desired.

title: quickie vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute onions and peppers.
Add Ragu sauce and vegetables; bring to a boil.
Stir in uncooked macaroni. Cook until tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: canned tomato soup
directions: Boil 45 minutes, then put through a sieve.
Cook and add 3 tablespoons cornstarch.
Boil 10 minutes more.
Put in jars and seal or it can be eaten right away.

title: fried squash
directions: Peel and slice squash into thin slices.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dip squash into mixture of eggs and milk.
Roll in bread crumbs and dip in milk a second time.
Roll squash in bread crumbs and drop into hot grease until brown, approximately 5 minutes.

title: preacher salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, drained pineapple and dry jello together. Stir in Cool Whip until all is blended well.
Store in refrigerator in a tight container.
Will keep up to a week.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups skim milk and sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Slice bananas on top, then 1/2 of the pudding mix.
Repeat again with wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Garnish top with crushed vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and salt.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Put all of mixture into a 1 gallon ice cream freezer.

title: pesto sauce for linguine
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in blender and cover.
With the blender running, slowly add corn oil. Blend 3 to 5 minutes until smooth. Stir in cheese. Toss with linguine.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine butterscotch, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, pecans and margarine.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Put in a large pan.
Let raise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mushrooms alex
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. Saute thinly sliced mushrooms until tender. Add Blue cheese and finely crumbled bacon. Stir until cheese is melted. Serve with toast rounds or crackers of your choice.

title: liver deluxe
directions: Dredge pieces of liver with flour and seasoning.
Brown gently on both sides in butter.
Make sauce by blending together the last 3 ingredients.
Pour over liver and cook 25 minutes on very low heat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour peaches and syrup in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk.
Blend until smooth. Pour over peaches.
Cut butter into small pieces and place over top of cobbler.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil water for noodles.
Cook until tender.
Drain off water from noodles.
Put in cans of mushroom soup, peas and tuna fish. Mix together.
Then serve.

title: ice cream in a can(great for picnic and creek bank)
directions: Put ingredients in 1 pound can and seal the lid.
Set the 1 pound can into the 3 pound can and pack the space around the can with ice and rock salt.
Put lid on 3 pound can.
Roll back and forth until ice cream is set.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: enchiladas with sour cream
directions: Heat tortillas on a hot griddle.
Keep warm.
Mix 1 cup of green chile sauce with chicken.
Put 1/4 cup chicken sauce mixture on each tortilla and roll up.
Place in baking dish, cover the enchiladas with the cheese.
Add the onion and salt to the remaining chili sauce and pour over the enchiladas.
Bake at 350 F for about 25 minutes.
Add sour cream on top of enchiladas and cook another 10 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in small amount of water until tender, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch and small amount of milk to desired consistency.
Add cheese, butter, salt and pepper. Heat on low until hot.
Do not boil.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on hot griddle until brown.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Use 1 cup of water and put in yeast.
Mix remaining water, salt, honey, butter and yeast mixture.
Mix in 1 cup flour at a time.
Occident and then whole wheat flour.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in salt water a few minutes to soften. Drain.
Mix all ingredients together except tomato soup.
Add to mixture 2 tablespoons soup and mix again.
Divide meat mixture into 8 equal parts.
Roll up in cabbage leaves.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place seam side down in casserole.
Cover with remaining tomato soup.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peek-a-boo oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt into a bowl.
Add sugar, shortening and water.
Beat until smooth, 2 minutes.
Fold in oats.
Spread on breadboard very thin.
Cut with cookie cutter. Cut a design in half of the cookies.
Place plain cookies on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon of jelly and cover with a designed cookie, lightly pressing edges together. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all but cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Pour remaining mixture on top and then add rest of cheese.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a large frying pan until white.
Drain. Mix together with all other ingredients.
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cheese last.
Heat oven to 350°. Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until done, lightly browned on top.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no-fat sweetened condensed milk
directions: Recipe from the kitchen of the Bible.
Start with one God the Father, and one Lord Jesus Christ.
Add honor to one father and one mother.
Stir in several obedient children.
Mix together all family members who are kind, tenderhearted, and thoughtful toward each other.
Add plenty of faith, hope
and love.

title: creole gumbo
directions: First you make the roux until dark brown.
Add onions, bell peppers, scallions, garlic and celery; cook until soft.
Add okra and cook until it loses it's gummy consistency.
Put this mixture into large stew pot.
Clean the skillet and fry bacon and diced ham slowly until browned.
Add ham and bacon to pot.
Season the beef cubes with seasoned flour, coating well.
Add to bacon grease and sear until brown; add to pot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in very large bowl.
Scrape out hole in the middle. Pour in wet ingredients and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour in 3 medium greased and floured loaf pans at 350°.

title: apple pancake
directions: Peel, core and slice apple.
Melt butter (in 10-inch skillet) over a medium flame.
Stir in cinnamon and sugar (1/4 cup). Arrange apple slices in skillet; cook for 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, beat flour, baking powder, salt and egg yolks until blended; set aside.
Fold egg whites with egg yolk mixture.
Spread evenly over apples.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain well.
Combine noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and onions in bowl; mix.
Spoon in a 6-cup shallow baking dish.
Top with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: orange walnut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Combine eggs, melted margarine, orange juice, orange peel and water.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir quickly until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Slice and serve with margarine.

title: easy baked fish fillets
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Place fish in a greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish. In a small bowl, combine lime juice, mayonnaise, onion powder and pepper. Spread over fish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs; drizzle with butter. Bake about 20 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until dissolved.
Add beer.
Pour over beef roast.
Marinate for 3 days, turning now and then.
At the end of 3 days, strain juice from meat.
Pat dry and flour the meat. Brown.
Add 1 cup juice and roast about 2 hours.
Don't let it go dry.
When tender, crush 16 or so gingersnaps in boiling juice and it will thicken into a gravy by itself.
Serve with Bread Dumplings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir eggs and sugar with spoon. Do not beat with mixer. Add syrup, margarine and pecans. Put in regular pie crust and bake at 350° until firm.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350 degrees in greased pan for 75 minutes.

title: angel hair pasta with veggies
directions: In frying pan, add 2 tablespoons of oil.
Sprinkle garlic.
Add red and yellow peppers, onion, mushrooms and zucchini.
Stir-fry. Heat tomatoes.
Pour all of above over angel hair pasta.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Finish filling 1 gallon freezer with milk.

title: glazed ginger pork
directions: To prepare the marinade, combine soy sauce, wine, honey, ginger and garlic, mix well.
Place roast in marinade, cover and let stand for about 8 hours, turning occasionally.
When ready to cook remove roast from the marinade, place on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Reserve 8 Tbsp of marinade for glaze, and the rest use for basting.
Bake at 300°F for about 2 1/2 hours or until done, basting several times.
Meat is ready when you insert a meat thermometer and it reads 175°.
For making the glaze combine 8 Tbsp marinade with currant jelly in a small saucepan.
Boil it over medium heat, for about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
After roast is cooked, spoon glaze over meat until completely coated.
Let cool.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: crunchy chix casserole
directions: Mix all together, except noodles. Spread 1/2 bag of chow mein noodles on bottom of buttered pan. Spread mixture over and top with remaining noodles.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour and buttermilk.
Add 1/2 cup hot water to the melted chocolate; place the other half in a separate pan and bring to a boil.
Add soda to the boiling water and immediately to the chocolate.
Add mixture to batter; add vanilla.
Bake at 325° until cake pulls from pans.

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: In a large bowl combine cauliflower, onion, all of the beans, pickles and carrots.
In a medium saucepan, bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour over vegetables; stir gently.
Cover and chill overnight. Stir again; drain before serving.
Yield:
12 to 18 servings.

title: saucy meat-n-mac
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain off fat.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix meat, macaroni and remaining ingredients except cheese in a large pan (9 x 13-inch). Sprinkle cheese on top and heat in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with Italian bread and salad. Great for a quick meal.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Blend at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured (I use Pam) 11 cup ring mold or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: clove julep
directions: Crush mint sprigs with sugar in the bottom of an 8-inch glass.
Add ice and vodka; stir and serve. Makes 1 serving.

title: stroganoff sandwich
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and Worcestershire sauce.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and mushrooms.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir in.
Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
(These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.)
Bake at 400° (moderate hot oven) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: stabilized whipped cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin over boiling water; cool.
Do not let congeal. Beat 1 cup of heavy cream until frothing; add cool gelatin very slowly to the cream as you continue beating.
When fluffy, but not stiff, add powdered sugar and beat cream until it holds shape in soft peaks; do not beat too long.
Watch it carefully.
Will hold up hours in the refrigerator.

title: hobgoblin brew
directions: Steep tea bags in hot water for 30 minutes. Remove bags. Add next 8 ingredients and simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Cut orange slices in half and insert whole cloves. Serve hot. Adjust ingredients to taste and add additional water. Keeps in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: pink almond pearls
