directions: Combine all
ingredients except icing in a medium sized bowl. Mix with
fork
to
blend
completely
(mixture will be stiff). Roll 1
teaspoon
at
a
time into marble sized balls between palms of hands.
Drop into Pink Icing.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: In a Dutch oven bring water and potatoes to a boil and cook until tender.
Add sausage, kraut, onion, garlic, dill and caraway.
Return to boiling.
In a small bowl mix sour cream and flour.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of hot soup mixture into sour cream mixture.
Return all to saucepan.
Blend well.
Heat through, not necessary to boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
If a less tart flavor is desired add a few teaspoons sugar.
Serve with dark bread or crackers.
Makes 8 to 10 cups.

title: spinach noodles
directions: Put olive oil in a skillet.
Saute together spinach, garlic (through press), basil and marjoram.
Add Romano cheese and hot red pepper.
Toss with cooked noodles.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg and beat well. Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thick. Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake on a lightly greased baking sheet at 350° about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until well blended.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir in kraut.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peppery scallops
directions: Rinse scallops and pat dry with paper towels.
In medium bowl, toss scallops with melted margarine to coat well.
On waxed paper, mix bread crumbs, dried basil, seasoned pepper and salt.
Dip one flat side of each scallop into bread crumb mixture.
Place scallops, breaded side up, on rack in broiling pan.
With broiling pan at closest position to source of heat, broil scallops 5 minutes without turning, until bread crumb topping is golden and scallops are opaque throughout.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oats and set aside.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt. Cream together the oleo, brown sugar and white sugar. Add the eggs and vanilla. Add the dry ingredients and oats.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut a pocket on the bone side of each chop.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper inside and out.
Saute onions and celery together in oil or bacon fat.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings and enough water to moisten (about 3 tablespoons).
Stuff into the chops through the opening that you cut.
Close the opening with toothpicks.

title: tiropet a kia(greek cheese triangles)
directions: Mix cheeses and eggs together.
If too stiff, add more eggs. Cut phyllo in strips, 5 or 6 lengthwise.
Cover unused strips with wax paper and damp cloth.
Brush entire strip with butter.
Put on teaspoon of cheese mixture on corner nearest you and fold corner over to form a triangle.
Continue folding pastry in triangles down the full length of strip (flag style) to make 1 multi-layered triangle.
Place on buttered baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water together.
Let cool. Add juice and Kool-Aid.
Pour ginger ale in immediately before serving. Different color can be made by changing flavor of Kool-Aid.
Float green sherbet in green punch.

title: sausage bar casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain really good. Add cream cheese and mix well. On a prepared baking sheet or casserole dish, lay 2 cans of crescent rolls out (DO NOT ROLL THEM), lay them where they form a single layer touching each other.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Pour mixture into prepared pie crust and bake at 325 degrees until set.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Lightly grease Bundt pan.
Place pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Arrange the frozen dough balls (12 to 14 frozen dough balls) on top of the pecans.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding on top of the dough.
In a small saucepan, cook and stir the butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until butter is melted.
Pour this mixture over pudding mix and dough balls in the Bundt pan.
Cover the pan with waxed paper and set in a cold oven to rise overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
When done, remove from oven and invert onto serving plate immediately.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: southwestern chicken salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, salsa and sour cream. Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Cream 1/2 cup pecans, flour and butter.
Press into 9 x 13 pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool crust.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and 1 cup 10x sugar.
Spread over crust.
Prepare instant pudding with 3 cups milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with pecans*. Cool overnight.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Mix pecans and coconut and spread on bottom of pan. Mix cake according to box directions, then pour over pecan/coconut mixture. Blend softened margarine, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. No need for frosting.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, olive oil, soy sauce and celery salt. Pour over beans, onion and water chestnuts.
Marinate overnight. Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make little 1-inch balls.
Put 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass covered in cinnamon-sugar.
Add more after flattening cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: auntie margie's aspic
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until aspic has started to set (about the consistency of an unbeaten egg white).
Then mix in the remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.
This recipe doubles well.

title: jello delight
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: brownies
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa and oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and last nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: white chocolate pecan mousse pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Cool.
Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat; stir in pecans.
Cook until pecans are golden brown. Cool at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: cape cod cranberry bread
directions: Wash, drain cranberries and set aside.
Mix the next 5 ingredients and put 2 tablespoons of this mixture aside to use later.
Cut oleo into flour mixture.
Beat together and add to flour the orange juice and egg.
Put 2 tablespoons of flour into a sack and add cranberries.
Shake until the berries are coated and fold into batter.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool in loaf pan and remove.
May add 1/2 cup nuts or 1 teaspoon grated peel to batter.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the ingredients well; add to unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes, or until it tests done in center. Makes 1 (10-inch) pie.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and margarine and mix well. Spread on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove and cool.
Combine strawberries, egg whites, sugar and vanilla in bowl and mix for 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped toping and mix well.
Sprinkle cookie mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish (reserve some topping for top).
Add strawberry mixture over cookie mixture.
Top with rest of cookie mixture and freeze overnight.
Remove 1 to 2 hours from freezer before serving.

title: dad's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Put in Dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on heat 1 to 2 hours.

title: seafood dip
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and cook on medium heat to golden brown. To this, add onions, celery and bell pepper; cook until tender. Add mushroom soup and your choice of seafood and cook on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Then add salt and pepper to taste.
I use Tony Chachere's Creole seasonings only.

title: angie's peach pie
directions: Melt butter in pan in oven.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Spoon drained fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Take half of cookie mix and spread on bottom of baking pan. Take cream cheese, egg and sugar and beat together.
Then put on top of cookie mix.
Take rest of cookie mix and spread on top.
If you desire, you can sprinkle nuts on top.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix well; spread between layers after cake has cooled.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sugar.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add egg mixture and beat until smooth.
Drop from funnel into deep hot oil or Crisco, swirling into 6-inch circles. Fry until golden brown.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Drain the artichokes and cut in half. Saute onions in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy meat balls
directions: In a sauce pan, mix BBQ sauce and jelly, heat together until jelly is melted.
If you're cooking the meat balls on the stove, heat the sauce and jelly in a pan large enough to hold all meat balls and sauce.
I use a crock pot, place the meat ball in a 3 or 4 qt crock pot, pour sauce over the balls, cook on high for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Turn down on low and continue to heat. Serve hot.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, then drain.
Add chicken soup and milk.
Stir.
Add Velveeta to taste.
Stir until warm.

title: favorite baked beans
directions: In small skillet partially cook bacon; drain and set aside. In a mixing bowl stir together pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, onion, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Lay the partially cooked bacon slices on top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 2 hours or until of desired consistency.
Serves 10.

title: hamburger-potato soup
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: bananas with peanuts
directions: To make the cooked dressing, mix the sugar, egg, vinegar and salt together and cook on low heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a light boil and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool or chill.

title: hot chocolate
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, pour water and add chocolate.
Microwave 5 minutes on High or until chocolate is melted.
Blend well.
Mix in sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High or until mixture begins to boil.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown bacon in skillet with onion; drain off grease.
Add catsup, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over green beans in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 250° for two hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (10-inch) pans or 1 Bundt pan.
In large mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Hand mix only.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven. Cool on rack 25 to 30 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Boil milk and cool.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour and knead. Let rise in bowl about 30 minutes.
Punch down and shape into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: barbara's irish creme
directions: Mix condensed milk, chocolate syrup and eggs in a blender. While blender is running, add whiskey and vodka.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate until used.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: potato noodles with garlic and wine beef
directions: Marinate beef cubes in soy sauce, garlic, red wine and black pepper for at least 2 hours, overnight for especially tough meat. Boil noodles in the 8 cups chicken broth until tender.
The noodles will enlarge and absorb all the liquid.
Boil on medium heat and keep covered to prevent broth from evaporating.
Cook vegetables in sesame oil in large pot until just soft, stirring constantly.
Spoon out vegetables and set aside.
Cook the marinated beef with the marinade sauce in the oil leftover from cooking the vegetables on medium heat, stirring constantly, until meat is cooked through.
Toss vegetables and meat together.
Serve in individual bowls by dishing out the meat and vegetables with some sauce over the noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, almonds and oleo, and place in greased casserole.
Put potato chips and almonds over top.
Pour over all oleo.
Bake 35 minute at 350°.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Crush crackers, add butter and sugar.
Mix well and line a 1 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan, reserving a small amount of crumbs for topping.
Dissolve each package of Jell-O in hot water and in separate bowls or flat pans.
Chill in pans until firm.
Then cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Soften plain gelatin in cold water; add hot pineapple juice and cool.
Whip cream and sugar and vanilla.
Fold in cooled gelatin and pineapple mixture.
Fold in Jell-O cubes; pour into crumb-lined pan.
Sprinkle on rest of crumbs; chill 6 to 8 hours until very firm.

title: orange date bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in dates, nuts and reserved orange rind.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine lemon peel, allspice, cloves and cinnamon in cheese cloth.
Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Serve hot.
Can store in refrigerator and reheat as needed.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Beat egg yolks and add rest of ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Better after 24 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together; bake at 400° about 30 minutes until tests done.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: bacon roll-ups(appetizer)
directions: Remove the crust from each slice of bread.
Spread with a thin layer of cream cheese.
Cut each slice of bread in thirds.
Cut a piece of raw bacon in thirds horizontally.
Roll a piece of the bread jelly roll fashion, then wrap a piece of bacon around it, securing with a toothpick.
Do this with the rest of the bread, cream cheese and bacon to produce as many as you need.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil until browned.
Turn to brown on other side. Serve hot.
These have to be watched as they burn easily!

title: tia lupe's homemade flour tortillas
directions: Thoroughly mix all dry ingredients with shortening in a mixing bowl.
Add warm water to mixture while kneading, until mixture is medium consistency (not as soft as biscuit dough).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Stir in all other ingredients; blend well.
Pour into two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk.
Combine flour and soda, then stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough 2 or more hours.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds.
Lay on greased sheet 1-inch apart.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.
(They freeze well.)

title: sherbet seltzer
directions: In a tall glass, place sherbet.
Stir in seltzer.
Place a straw into the glass.
Serve, sip and relax.

title: salad seasoning blend
directions: Combine together and spoon into shaker or tightly covered container.
Makes 1 cup.
Sprinkle over salad greens, sliced tomatoes, cold vegetables or cottage cheese.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Cut lobster meat into 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add cream and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Add lobster meat; heat.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in sherry.
Serve immediately on toast points or in patty shells.
Serves 6.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients, except jam; mix well.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll in balls. Press down and put thumbprint in middle.
Fill middle with seedless raspberry jam.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
While hot sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube 12 ounces of chicken breast.
Mix chicken, bread, celery and onion in a casserole dish.
Pour chicken broth over all ingredients and stir gently.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour or until lightly browned crust forms on top.
Serves 4 for lunch.

title: rice nut loaf with tomato sauce
directions: Cream together peanut butter and water.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
(May use package of George Washington broth instead of salt and sage.)
Mixture is quite thin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Double this recipe to fill bread pan that has been well-greased and crumbed. Turn out onto platter.
Pour a can of heated undiluted tomato soup for sauce.
(Said to be a favorite of E. G. White.)

title: kringla
directions: Mix as for cake.
Chill well.
Place a tablespoon of dough on lightly floured cloth.
Roll pencil thin, 12 inches long.
Make into a figure 8.
Bake on greased sheet for 12 minutes at 425°.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Mix oil with garlic, soy sauce and lemon juice; set aside. Score meat on both sides; baste with lemon mixture and place on grill.
Partially cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes on each side. Turn 3 to 4 times; baste occasionally.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put in a 2-quart casserole the zucchini, eggs, mushroom soup, mayonnaise, chopped onion and salt and pepper. Top with grated cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with Pepperidge Farm dressing and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Good with broccoli or spinach.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream, chocolate pieces and candy bars to mixture; beat until creamy and add pecans.
Cool slightly for 20 minutes; stir mixture and pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut.
Yields 4 pounds.

title: pretty good cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and soda; sprinkle over filling.
In bowl, combine eggs, vanilla and oil; mix well.
Pour over other ingredients.
Stir only until blended in pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Ice with ready made cream cheese frosting.
May be served warm, unfrosted, with ice cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cream shortening and sugar. Beat eggs just enough to break yolk. Add to shortening and sugar. Add flour and milk alternately, then vanilla. Kneed slightly on floured board. Roll and cut with cookie cutter. Preheat oven to 400 degrees and reduce to 350 degrees when the cookies are put in oven. Bake on a greased cookie sheet about 15 minutes. Makes about 9 dozen, depending on thickness.

title: gelatin fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add frozen strawberries. Stir until thawed; add bananas, pineapple and raisins.
Pour 1/2 in large bowl; chill until firm.
Add 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Add remainder of mixture.
Chill, then add remainder of Cool Whip, then refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: italian spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly and get hot.
Place on very low heat for about 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.
Cook fine spaghetti according to box directions (1/2 pound).

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Gradually blend sugar into cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook and mash squash.
Add remaining ingredients and spread bread crumbs in buttered dish.
Pour in squash mixture and top with more bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces, combine flour, salt, pepper, Pound mixture into meat. Melt shortening and brown meat on both sides. Add remaining ingredients; cover and bake at 325° for 1 hr.

title: hot mustard
directions: Whisk together mustard and vinegar and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Mix together sugar and eggs; add pat of butter.
Add mustard mixture.
Cook over medium heat until spoon is coated. Great dip for hors d'oeuvres or pretzels.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain on paper towels and transfer to wax paper.
Brown 1 pound beef; drain.
Add Ragu sauce and simmer until heated thoroughly.
Grease a Pyrex dish and pour in enough meat sauce to cover bottom.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of meat mixture evenly down center of entire length of noodle.
Roll up and place seam side down in greased baking dish.
Repeat for number of noodles desired.
Pour remaining beef mixture over noodles.

title: ole settlers baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Then add all except last 4 ingredients and mix well.
Pour all ingredients into large baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
May be frozen before or after baking.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil; cook for a few minutes, then set aside to cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and carrots.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Add frosting.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chinese plum sauce
directions: Remove pits from plums.
Puree plums and syrup in blender. In saucepan, saute onion in oil until softened.
Add remaining ingredients including pureed plums and cook until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Use to glaze pork or poultry.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.

title: spiced pineapple punch
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices in saucepan.
Place over low heat; boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Strain and cool.
Add fruit juices.
Pour over ice in pitcher or punch bowl.
Makes 3 to 10 servings.

title: sesame cabbage salad
directions: Brown sesame and almonds together separately.
Mix cabbage and onions together.
Just before serving, mix almonds, sesame seed and the crushed uncooked noodles.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes and liquid.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Cook to boiling point, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes, with pot covered.
Add shrimp and cook until heated through.
Garnish servings with crumbled bacon (1/3 cup dry white wine may be added before serving). Yields 4 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: You will also need a buttered small bowl.

title: 15 minute preserves
directions: Place ingredients in large pot.
Cool on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil 15 minutes on high.
Skim.
Let stand for 4 to 6 hours.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 pints. (Strawberries, blueberries or blackberries may be used.)

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into crusts and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Peel and slice squash, removing seed.
Cook until tender with 1/2 cup water.
Drain.
Puree in electric mixer or blender; must be very smooth.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook 3 slices bacon; crumble.
Brown onion and pepper in drippings.
Stir in beans; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 2 slices uncooked bacon. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: roasted sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in one layer in a lightly buttered baking dish. Dot with butter and roast in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, tossing every 10 minutes and adding more butter, if necessary.
Serve hot with salt and pepper to taste.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and stir.
Chill.
Serve with a variety of raw vegetables that can be dipped.

title: zebra brownies
directions: Grease bottom only of 9x13 pan.
Mix filling ingredients and set aside.

title: zucchini and ham
directions: Cut zucchini in chunks, boil for about 15 minutes. Drain well. Put zucchini, ham, scallions, salt and pepper in casserole dish and cover with sliced cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, juice (from cans of fruit), flour and salt.
Bring to a boil until thick and yellow.
Cook macaroni; rinse and drain.
Let cool.
Add to cooked mixture.
Mix together well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple the next morning.

title: wanda's original strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package; refrigerate. Mix ice milk and strawberries in a large punch bowl.
Pour cold Kool-Aid over strawberries and ice milk.
Add ginger ale to mixture.

title: butter frosting
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in large saucepan; stir well. Place over medium heat and bring to a boil until soft ball stage. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff peaks form.
Continue to beat while slowly adding hot mixture.
Beat until mixture cools and thickens.

title: rice pilaf
directions: *Bell peppers can be any color, but should be cut into 1-inch julienne strips.

title: tuna asparagus casserole
directions: *Use standard white sauce recipe.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Season beans and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain and place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water; pour over beans.
Top mixture with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mud
directions: Smash cookies (you can use food processor); add melted butter and mix together.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Press cookies in pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream; spread on top of cookies.
Spread hot fudge after you have put the layer of ice cream on.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze for 1 to 2 hours.

title: five can casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef. Combine first 6 ingredients. Cover bottom of casserole dish with sauce. Add layer of tortillas; cover with sauce and cheese.
Repeat until all the sauce is used and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until the cheese has melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add eggs to mixture and beat for 1 minute.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie(dessert)
directions: In saucepan, combine corn syrup, sugar and butter; bring to boil.
Boil gently, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Prepare pie crust.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Flute edges.
Place pecans in flat.
Combine eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour cool syrup mix into eggs and beat well.
Pour over nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: candy
directions: In a double boiler, heat evaporated milk.
In a saucepan, melt 1 cup sugar until it is a rich brown, slowly stir in boiling mandarin juice.
Add this mixture to the hot milk.
Stir in 2 cups sugar and salt.
Cook this syrup slowly to the soft ball state. Stir frequently, add the mandarin peel.
Cool.
Beat the mixture until it is creamy.
Add nut meats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3/4 pound.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, salt, eggs, and vinegar and coconut, pecans and raisins. Pour into crust baked at 325° for 35- 40 min.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Beat eggs well with fork.
Add remaining ingredients using fork or hand mixer.
Do not use electric mixer.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° until center is firm.

title: cookies-n-cream ice cream
directions: Whip eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually until thick.
Add remaining ingredients (use the 6 cup milk fill line on freezer canister).

title: easy onion baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate slices, slightly overlapping in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix vegetables, chicken, soup and onion together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix flour, mayonnaise and milk together (mixture will be very thin) and pour over mixture in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, or until crust is golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate sharp and
cheddar cheese and onion.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Shape into balls, sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap in foil to store.
Serve with celery or crackers.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in a Pyrex dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over firm mixture.
Add the rest of the mixture on top of sour cream.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: peanut butter ice cream sauce
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, margarine and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave at High setting 4 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring after 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, stir until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 3 cups. Store in refrigerator if any leftover.
To reheat, microwave at Medium setting 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Do not boil.
Also good on pound cake and as vegetable sauce.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice until soft.
Then add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put into a 2-quart well-greased casserole.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Dip eggplant in butter, then in mixture of bread crumbs and salt.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Spoon sauce on top of each slice; sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: meat 'n tater pie
directions: Brown potatoes thoroughly.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine meat, milk, soup mix, pepper and allspice.
Mix gently.
Lightly pat into pastry-lined pie plate.
Top with potatoes.
Place top crust over potatoes.
Seal with flute edges. Cut design in top of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
Serve with warm catsup if desired.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli; add all other ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown sausage or ground turkey; add onion and cook until tender.
(You can rinse and drain to get rid of some of the fat.) Add potatoes, water, salt, marjoram and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add milk and corn.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut corned beef spread
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, nuts and raisins.
Roll in small balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, milk and strawberries. Add Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt cele's cucumber salad
directions: Cook until sugar melts and pour over raw tomatoes, onion and cucumbers.
Chill.

title: triple treat cookies
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Beat next 5 ingredients until fluffy.
Add peanut butter.
Stir nuts and chocolate chips in last.
Shape in little balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
May be mixed and refrigerated overnight.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in egg, onion, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix well, then add 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Stir and pour in greased pan.
Melt butter; pour over remaining cracker crumbs and sprinkle over corn mixture. Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Garnish with pimento strips.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Stir sugar, salt and vinegar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 5 days.
Keeps well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in butter in skillet.
Take meat out of pan. Combine mushrooms and green onions; saut until tender.
Add beef broth until boiling.
Add sour cream.
Add flour and mix in meat. Stir until sauce thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In separate pan, boil egg noodles until tender.
Serve stroganoff over cooked egg noodles.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, garlic and green pepper in a 4-quart saucepan over high heat until beef is browned, about 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, tomato paste, brown sugar, oregano and paprika.
Heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in kidney beans with their liquid; heat thoroughly.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, gently combine potatoes and eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and onion; stir into potato mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a preheated nonstick skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray. Brown lightly on both sides.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be used for muffins (reduce baking time to 45 minutes).

title: coconut cake icing
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, then pour powdered sugar over egg whites slowly and mix.
Then add Crisco.
Last put vanilla and salt in egg whites as you beat egg.
Mix real good when you add Crisco, then spread on cake.
Put fresh coconut on cake.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, salt and onion and let stand 3 hours. Drain and rinse with cold water. Add other ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. Place in hot jars and seal.

title: friendly fruit spritzer
directions: Combine juice and club soda.
Serve over ice.
Yield: 1 (8 ounce) serving, 60 calories/cup.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut apples in 1/4 and wrap them in rolls.

title: bran muffins
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients together; set aside.
Mix Bran and milk; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add oil and egg; mix well. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: lamb chops with rosemary
directions: Heat oven to
Spray
cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Beat egg
with
fork
in
a medium sized bowl. Add remaining ingredients
and	mix until well blended.
Shape in eight 1/2-inch patties.
Place on prepared cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12
minutes,	turning
once,	until golden brown on both sides.

title: creamy lentil soup
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add next 3 ingredients; saute 3 minutes.
Add cumin and curry powder; cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly.
Add lentils and next 3 ingredients; stir well and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until lentils are tender, stirring occasionally.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into electric blender or food processor, cover and process until smooth.
Repeat with remaining lentil mixture.
Return mixture to pan; cook over medium heat until heated.
Spoon into soup bowls and top with yogurt.

title: aunt sally's cocoa drops
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Add nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and butter.
Add tomato sauce and set aside to cool.
Cook noodles.
Mix meat, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green peppers.
Put half of noodles in bottom of greased casserole.
Add cheese.
Mix and add balance of noodles.
Do not stir.
Add meat and melted butter on top.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Cook
macaroni shells until half done; remove from heat and drain. Rinse in cool water; separate and set aside on rack to cool.
Brown
sausage
and	beef in skillet; drain and put aside. Simmer
spaghetti
sauce
with green pepper, onion and mushrooms until
vegetables are tender.
Blend together thoroughly
meat, cottage
cheese,
egg
and	crumbs.
Spoon some spaghetti
sauce into the bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish or pan.	Preheat
oven to	350°.
Stuff
each
shell
with large spoonful of
meat mixture.
Place
in
single layer in baking dish and
spoon spaghetti
sauce
over the top of the shells, making sure
all shells
are
covered.
Bake about 30 minutes until	shells	are cooked
thoroughly.
Remove
from oven and sprinkle
Mozzarella cheese over top.
Place under broiler for a few seconds until cheese is melted.
Serve and enjoy.

title: no bake fudgy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a full boil then boil for 1 minute.
Time accurately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to become firm, approximately 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add sugar or sweetener to taste. Add water; serve hot or cold.

title: upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet or square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch) in the oven until melted. Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Arrange pineapple slices on top.
Place a cherry in center of each pineapple slice.
Beat remaining ingredients in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, scraping the bowl occasionally.
Pour over fruit in skillet. Spread evenly.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes in skillet or 55 to 60 minutes in square pan.
Immediately turn the skillet upside down on a heatproof plate.
Let the skillet remain over the cake a few minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: pawley's inn crab cakes
directions: Mix well.
Gently fold crabmeat into mayo mixture.
Divide into 6 equal portions.
Form into patties.
Roll carefully in fresh cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate at least one hour before cooking. Just before cooking, re-roll in bread crumbs.
Saute crab cakes in 3 tablespoons butter for 2 minutes.
Turn carefully and saute for 2 minutes more.
Serve with lemon wedges, melted butter and tartar sauce.

title: quick pizza for children
directions: Top with any topping desired:
olives, pepperoni, onion, sausage, etc.
Bake on cookie sheet in oven at 400° until cheese is bubbly.

title: bi-cracky bars
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Place 1/3 of the batter in a small bowl and add 1 ounce of unsweetened chocolate and walnuts.
In 2/3 batter bowl, add the chocolate chips.
Spread the 1/3 chocolate batter mixture in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange graham crackers on top of chocolate batter, then spread white batter
with chocolate chips on top of graham crackers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler.
Do not place over boiling water now; beat on low speed for 1/2 minute.
Place over boiling water, but not touching the water.
Cook and beat until frosting forms peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat an additional 2 minutes on high.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and shredded cheese in bowl; mix well. Add spices to taste.
Moisten hands with water and shape cheese into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in skillet.
Add eggs and salt.
Fry until firm.
Remove to plate.
Cut into strips and reserve.
Heat remaining 5 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Saute just until tender and crisp.
Add rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Stir in soy sauce and eggs.
Taste.
Add more soy sauce, if desired.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients, add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms parma
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms.
Chop stems; combine with cheese, margarine and onion.
Fill mushroom caps with this mixture.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush Oreos in blender or zip lock bag with rolling pin until they resemble potting soil.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugar add cream cheese.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, make pudding according to directions on box.
Blend in cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in flower pot as follows:
Oreos (about 1/4 of cookies), pudding mixture, pie filling, pudding mixture, pie filling, pudding mixture, remaining Oreos.
Decorate with silk flowers and serve with a spade.
(If you are really brave, add gummy worms to soil.)

title: microwave tea
directions: Heat water in microwave for 7 minutes on High (small Tupperware pitcher works well).
Place tea bags in water to steep. Remove bags; add sugar to taste.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool; remove from pan.

title: corn bread(servings:  10)
directions: Blend oil and honey together.
Beat in egg, baking powder and salt.
Add both flours, then milk; mix until nearly smooth.
Pour into well oiled cast-iron skillet.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in 1 cup milk.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until firm.
Very good!

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Drain squash leaving about 1/3 of its juice in each can.
In large bowl, mix together onion, squash, cream of chicken soup, salt, pepper and garlic powder with corn bread.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cheddar cheese may be added on top.
Cook for about 5 more minutes if desired.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk together for 6 minutes.
Pour over the following ingredients which have been mixed together in a bowl:
nuts, butter, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan to cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Beat eggs real good.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Finish filling with whole milk.

title: norma's easy one dish meal
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Push meat to sides and saute the onion.
Add catsup, spices and water.
Simmer 30 minutes. While meat is still cooking, cook the macaroni and drain. Add macaroni and beans to meat. Correct seasonings and simmer 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a separate large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars together; then beat in egg. Beat in vanilla and milk.
Stir the dry ingredients into the butter-sugar mixture, stirring until well blended.
Fold in the oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop the dough by teaspoons onto the prepared baking sheets, approximately 2 inches apart.
Bake about 12 minutes, or until the edges of the cookies are browned.
With a spatula, remove the cookies to a wire rack.
When cool, store in tightly covered tins in a cool place.
(Can be frozen up to 2 to 3 weeks, if wrapped well.)

title: italian chicken with vegetables(for microwave only)
directions: Note:
You can substitute other fresh vegetables as you prefer.

title: nutmeg delight cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Press half the crumb mixture on bottom of greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Stir baking soda into sour cream.
To remaining crumbs add sour cream, egg and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over crust.
Top with nuts.
Bake 25 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into greased pan. Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour this mixture on top of the cake mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Add all ingredients, then flour.
Add vanilla and nuts and beat well. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Cool and cut into squares. Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and spread deboned chicken over roll and roll up into a roll; repeat until you use all rolls.
Place in dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and 3 cans chicken broth.
Pour over rolls and bake at 400° until brown.
You can use cheese sauce. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in baking dish, 8 x 8 inch or larger.
Cut crust from bread and cut each slice in 5 strips. Place bread strips over peaches.
Mix sugar, flour, egg, margarine and peach juice.
Pour over bread strips.
Bake 35-45 minutes until golden brown.

title: maple apple ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apples in bottom of loaf pan. Pour maple syrup over them to cover.
Mix ham and beef thoroughly. Combine bread crumbs, milk, eggs, onion and mustard.
Mix well; add to meat.
Pack meat mixture over apples, pressing firmly with hand. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Drain off excess fat. Allow loaf to stand out of oven for 10 minutes before unmolding and slicing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt and pepper together and drain; set aside.
Mix pizza sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar and spices together with drained hamburger and macaroni.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Put the remaining mixture in the pan.
Arrange pepperoni slices on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan or 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Grease an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Spread cherries over bottom. Sprinkle cake crumbs over cherries.
Drop pads of butter on crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in large (12-quart) pot.
Cover with ample water (8-quarts).
Add salt.
Bring to boil and turn down to simmer and skim off fat.
Add parsley, celery, carrots, tomatoes, onions and allspice.
Once all the vegetables are in, bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer for 3 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Rinse spinach thoroughly and pat dry.
Place in a bowl and refrigerate while preparing eggs and bacon.
Mix chopped eggs, crumbled bacon, oil, salt and pepper and let stand until ready to serve.
Add the mixture to the salad and toss well.
Top with anchovies, if desired.

title: hot crab canapes
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Stir well; set aside. Trim crust from bread; cut each slice into 4 squares.
Spread each square with crabmeat mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
6 1/2 dozen appetizer servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and chilies in bowl.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer strips of tortilla, chicken mix and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: broccoli-noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Return to saucepan.
In skillet with hot salad oil, cook carrots, mushrooms, onion and salt over medium-high heat until tender.
Stir in broccoli.
Stir in milk and undiluted soup.
Heat through.
Stir soup mixture into noodles.
Spoon into casserole.

title: nudes potato salad dressing
directions: Put vinegar, water, sugar and egg in saucepan.
Stir, bring to a boil then add salad dressing, mustard and milk.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes together with other ingredients.
Slice or chop pepperoni.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Balls may be rolled in nuts, coconut or powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tuna chip casserole
directions: Line bottom of 2-quart casserole with 1/2 cup of the potato chips.
Mix tuna and cream of mushroom soup together in a separate bowl; pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, add 2 cups of water and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil.
Wash and slice squash and zucchini.
Add to boiling water with carrots.
Cook 5 minutes, uncovered, mixing while cooking so it will cook evenly.
Don't overcook.
Drain.
In bowl, combine soup, sour cream and onions.
Fold squash mixture in.
Combine melted butter and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 of the stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture on top of stuffing mix.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: mary's strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: world's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand at least 2 hours or overnight.
When ready to make cookies, cream together shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Sift salt, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Stir flour mixture into sugar-shortening mixture and blend well.
Beat egg-raisin mixture into mixture. Add oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Dough will be stiff.
Chill dough for a better shaped cookie.
Drop dough by spoonful on cool ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
This is a chewy cookie.

title: charcoal chicken
directions: Cut fryers in half and cut wings off.
Put in skin and sprinkle liberally with garlic salt and lemon pepper.

title: best ever banana pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan; cook until thick.
Pour over cookies and bananas.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over cauliflower and broccoli.
Mayonnaise may be used instead of salad dressing.
Six packages Sweet 'N Low may be used instead of sugar.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, molasses and eggs.
Add hot water, then flour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Makes a big cake.

title: peanut butter cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg; beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, until set and beginning to brown.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix graham crackers, brown sugar and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Pour over graham cracker mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, top with blueberry pie filling.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in large pan. Add cereal and stir gently until coated. Place sugar in large bag and add cereal mixture. Shake until coated. Pour in to 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix and store in dry container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: ice ring punch
directions: Mix all frozen juices and cherries with water to bring to 64 ounces. Freeze in a ring mold.

title: fantastic teriyaki marinade for grilled meats
directions: In a large, shallow plastic or glass container, combine 1/2 bottle of sauce, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Float onion and garlic in mixture; stir.
Add meat (steak, boneless chicken, chicken wings, pork and/or lamb); up to 3 pounds.
Add water until mixture covers meat.
Stir around meat well to blend in water.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight, turning meat in marinade occasionally.

title: pineapple chicha(drink)
directions: Cut and slice pineapple into chunks.
Blend in blender 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Strain and place in pitcher.
Add sugar, water and ice.
This is a very popular tropical drink.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and onion.
Add egg and mix well.
Add liquid and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into deep fat at 375° or into skillet with 1-inch fat.
Fry each side until brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Bake in tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.
Test with pick.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally into thin slices.
Cut into 2-inch pieces. Preheat electric frypan at 375°.
Add oil, salt and pepper; heat. Add meat.
Cook until brown.
Set control at 210°.
Add onion, garlic, green peppers, celery and bouillon; cover and cook until vegetables are crisp, about 10 minutes.
Add hot water if necessary.
Blend cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce.
Add to meat.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve with steaming hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese sit out to soften.
Chop about 1/2 of the tops of the green onions fine (do not use the bottoms of the onions).
Mix cream cheese, corned beef and onion tops together. Form into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
Pour off grease.
In a large pot, combine hamburger meat and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Stir frequently.
Turn heat to low and simmer about 2 hours.
Stir frequently.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased pan. Flatten with floured or powdered sugared fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain grease.
Add all ingredients together in large pot.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: "surprise" dogs 'n cheese
directions: Take hot dog, put slice of cheese around hot dog.
Place in microwave for 1 minute on High (or until cheese melts).
Ready to eat.

title: blue cheese mayonnaise
directions: Press crumbled Blue cheese through fine sieve.
Mix with mayonnaise and milk.
Add Tabasco sauce and mix well.

title: crab bisque
directions: Mix together potato soup, corn, chopped onion, milk and nutmeg in a large pot.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add crabmeat/imitation. Simmer 15 more minutes, stirring regularly.
Mix in parsley and serve.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Follow cooking directions. When cooled, split layers.
Cool cake completely before splitting layers.

title: parmesan meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese. Lightly pack in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle top with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut in squares.

title: teresa's famous crock-pot dish
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onion in skillet and drain.
Mix beans and seasoning in crock-pot while meat is browning.
Add meat, then cut up sausage in small slices and add.
Mix well and cook on low to medium heat for 8 to 10 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan according to directions on box.
After cake cools, crumble half of cake in punch bowl or large bowl.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cook until soft ball.
Remove from heat. Add the vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until creamy. Pour in dish. Cut in squares. Add nuts, if desired.

title: doug's b.b.q. ribs
directions: Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, Vickers BBQ sauce, and 1 tablespoon lemon juice to make a paste. Mop mixture on ribs and cook at 225° to 250° for 4 hours on indirect heat on the grill. Baste occasionally during this time. Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, Vickers and Kraft BBQ sauce. Baste the ribs with this mixture 1 hour before removing from the grill. Total cooking time 5-6 hours.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix the ingredients together until smooth and spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake in 400° oven for about 12 minutes or until brown.

title: cinnamon punch
directions: Combine the sugar, candy and water together until candy is melted.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir for 3 minutes.
Add frozen fruit.
Stir until fruit thaws and mixture begins to thicken.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and orange rind in a small bowl. Separate each biscuit.
Place a cream cheese square in center of one-half and top with remaining half, pinching sides together. Dip in butter and dredge in sugar mixture.

Stand each biscuit on "edge" in a lightly greased 12-cup Bundt pan, spacing evenly. Drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately invert onto a wire rack (or plate). Combine powdered sugar and orange juice. Spoon over warm bread. Serve immediately. Yields 1 (10-inch) coffee cake.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, unsweetened cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
In another bowl, whisk egg whites with water and corn syrup.
Stir wet ingredients into dry and mix until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch square pan, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 16.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together in this order.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: punch(approximately 9 quarts, 30 people, about 90 cups)
directions: Boil skins in 2 quarts water for 15 minutes.
Use only one or two grapefruit skins.
Squeeze out skins and add all this to fruit juice.
Dissolve sugar before adding.

title: "try-and-guess" salad-theresa shea
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the hot water.
Stir in the stewed tomatoes, breaking them into bits with a spoon.
Add the hot pepper sauce.
Pour into a lightly oiled 3-quart mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on greens.
Place a small bowl in the center and fill with the sour cream, horseradish, salt and sugar.
Serves 12.

title: dump cake
directions: Note: Do not mix anything.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Butter	both
sides
of
bread with melted butter.
Cut each slice
into
6 strips.
Alternate apples, bread and raisins.
Beat eggs,
milk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread, apples and raisins.
Bake in Pyrex casserole (rectangle).
Set in large
pan of water to bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hurry curry
directions: Saute onion and curry in margarine. When onion is soft, add soup, mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and chicken. Stir until smooth (it will be thick).
Lastly, add chicken bouillon for flavoring. Simmer mixture for 2 minutes. Serve over hot noodles or rice. Can garnish with bananas, chutney or coconut.
Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In large bowl, sift dry ingredients together. Add Crisco and yeast mixture. Work with hands until moistened and dough stays together. Do not overmix; mix just until dough is no longer sticky. Place dough in a greased Tupperware bowl. Grease top of dough, cover with waxed paper and seal with a tight lid. Keep in refrigerator. Will keep for 4 weeks or more. When wanting biscuits, remove as much dough as you think you will need from the bowl. (Cover remaining dough with waxed paper and lid; store in refrigerator until you are ready to make more.) Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick. Melt a little oleo in microwave. Cut biscuits with a biscuit cutter and fold in half, pocketbook style. Dip in butter and place on cookie sheet. Bake on third rack in oven at 400° until lightly browned.

title: microwave brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart pot, stir sugar and syrup well and cook on High in microwave oven for 4 minutes and 10 seconds.
Stir in nuts and cook on High 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla and blend well.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda until foamy; stir well.
Pour quickly onto buttered cookie sheet.
Smooth mixture into a thin layer.
Be careful, peanut brittle is very hot and sticky.
Cool 1 hour.
Lift brittle onto bread board; break into pieces.
Store in airtight container. Makes 1 pound.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Stir in marshmallows.
Put Crisco, Coke and cocoa in a 2-cup glass measure.
Heat in microwave until Crisco melts, 2 minutes.
Pour over flour mixture. Stir in buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Pour into a greased glass dish.
Cook on High for 11 minutes.
Turn dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Frost with Coca-Cola Icing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice; set pineapple aside. Add enough water to the juice to measure 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring well until gelatin dissolves.
Add cranberry sauce, stirring until blended.
Stir in ginger ale, pineapple and celery.
Pour mixture into a lightly oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and chill until firm.
Yields 15 servings.

title: creamy chicken parmesan
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Dip chicken in egg, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in microwave-safe dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High about 10 minutes or until no longer pink.
Mix together soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Cover and cook another 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs.
Serve, eat and enjoy.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Steam broccoli.
Add all ingredients to onion and heat until cheese melts.
Stir often.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all together until smooth.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook for 3 minutes; add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Pour out in a 1/2-quart casserole dish and let cool.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Drain (dry) can
of
pineapple;
chop
pineapple.
Bake yellow Jiffy cake mix
as	directed, using pineapple juice for liquid. Cool.
Mix pudding	as
directed.
Add
cream cheese, spread over cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pineapple and chopped pecans.	Top with Cool Whip.
Top with toasted coconut.	Chill overnight. Keeps well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: clam dabbies
directions: Mash cheese and blend with all ingredients except clams. Drain clams and add.
Put toast on cookie sheet and cover with clam spread.
Broil until lightly brown.

title: brownies
directions: Beat
with
mixer
the following:
eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
(Stir cocoa and flour together before you start the recipe.) Mix
well
and
add
nuts
and chocolate syrup last. After
all ingredients added, beat well.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. (I bake at 350°.)

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add cheese and corn.
Layer in loaf pan size casserole dish:
1 layer of peppers, 1 layer of corn, peppers, corn, peppers and corn.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: green rice bake
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and chop.
Saute onion in oleo.
Stir in rice, soup and broccoli; mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: ginger sauce
directions: Fortune cookies may be purchased from any Oriental market or restaurant.
I have purchased them from distributing companies that handle food stuffs in packets for restaurants.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Beat egg white, add sugar and beat until stiff.
Roast raw peanuts until light brown stirring often.
Pour hot peanuts into egg white mixture and spread on a cookie sheet to cool.
Mix cooled nuts with red and green M&M's for a great Christmastime snack.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding mix. Add milk, oil and eggs. Mix well. Pour into 3 cake pans. Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until tests done.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add tomatoes, soup and water.
Heat until bubbly.
Add shrimp until pink.
Then add Velveeta cheese and spaghetti.
Place in a casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over and top with grated cheese. Heat in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Slice margarine and dot top of mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until liquid absorbs.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salad dressing.
Mix well. Pour salad dressing over mixture.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours before serving.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: kate's beets with orange sauce
directions: Cook beets, then set aside and keep hot.
Combine rest of ingredients and cook about 4 minutes, stirring often.
Stir into beets.

title: beef casserole chinese style
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish. Cover with peas, then celery.
Mix soup, salt, pepper, milk and onion.
Pour over the meat.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Place a heavy skillet (cast iron) on medium heat, add butter and let it melt. Peel
the potato and slice into slices about 1/3 inch thick.
Place into hot skillet and cook slowly so the butter does not burn.
Brown on each side.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Some people sprinkle them with just a light dusting of sugar just as they remove them but I do not.

title: millionaires chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar and Milnot 10 minutes and add to other ingredients which have been broken and combined in a large mixing bowl. Cut margarine in small chunks and add pecans last.
Stir and turn into greased dish.
Cut into squares before completely set.

title: easy pie crust for fresh fruit pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together in pie pan.
Whip oil and milk together and mix with dry mixture in pie pan to form soft dough.
Press with fingertips to form pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and cook, beating while cooking.
Add dash of salt and pepper.
Cool and stir into grated cabbage.

title: oyster stew
directions: Saute oysters with butter and salt and pepper to taste. Add heated milk to mixture.
Do not boil.

title: ma-ma's peppy pickled eggs
directions: Place split garlic cloves, bay leaf and pepper pod in large jar.
Fill jar with peeled, hard-boiled eggs.
Heat vinegar with remaining spices and pour into jar over eggs.
Cap.
Shake gently and refrigerate for a week to allow flavors to blend.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter until mixture is fluffy.
Add milk and whipped topping; beat until mixture is smooth.
Spoon into the graham cracker crust.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks, then beat until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and mix until smooth.
Mix jam, raisins and nuts in by hand.
Fold in well beaten egg whites; mix thoroughly.
Bake until done at 300° (between 2 1/2 and 3 hours, depending upon your stove).

title: cheese chowder soup
directions: Cook and drain the vegetables well.
Combine this with soup and milk in saucepan.
Heat to simmering, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with toss salad and wheat or white crackers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream brunch coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Heavily grease Bundt pan and using part of the mixture, coat all sides of pan.
Use remaining for layering with batter.
(I use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.)
Combine the rest of the ingredients and beat until creamy.
Alternate layers of batter with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (I bake for 40 to 45 minutes).
Cool well before removing from pan.

title: easy strawberry banana dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Crumble into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Prepare pudding as directed. Set aside.
Thinly slice strawberries and bananas.
In large bowl or pan layer pudding, cake, Cool Whip, strawberries and bananas.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken.
Put chicken, water and bouillon cubes in gumbo pot.
Boil with carrots, celery and bay leaves.
Remove bay leaves and discard.
Remove chicken; debone and set aside.
Mix the flour, egg and enough water to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto a floured surface and roll very thin.
Cut in 1/2-inch squares.
Drop in boiling broth.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Return chicken to pot and serve.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Mix ham, Velveeta
and bread crumbs; place on flattened chicken breasts.
Tuck
edges
together and fasten with toothpick, if necessary.
Dip	in melted butter and place in baking dish (edges down).
Add	sherry	or
wine
and bouillon cubes. Cover and cook for 45
minutes
at
Drain	3/4
cup
of liquid for gravy.	Continue
to cook chicken for 30 minutes or until done and slightly
brown.
Mix the flour, cold water and Kitchen Bouquet and
stir
into
chicken
broth.
Add mushroom pieces and cook
until
gravy thickens.
Place chicken breasts on bed of cooked wild
rice.	Spoon gravy over and serve while hot.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Rinse sauerkraut twice. Wash mushrooms. Cover sauerkraut and mushrooms with water and cook until tender (about 1 1/2 hours). Chop onion and fry in butter and add to soup.
Brown flour in the other tablespoon of butter until nut brown.
Pour 3 tablespoons of soup into the browned flour.
Mix and add to soup. Bring to boiling point and serve.

title: lowbush cranberry nut bread with simple cranberry sauce
directions: Grate the rind and squeeze the juice from both oranges and put in a measuring cup.
Add additional liquid (juice or milk) to make a total of 2 cups.
Mix liquid, butter, sugar and eggs in a bowl. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir briefly.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best when it is cooled and wrapped overnight before slicing.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Mix egg yolks with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Add butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Brown in 325° oven.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add cornbread mix.
Stir well. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer:
1/2 cake (crumbled), pineapple, pie filling, pudding, coconut and remaining half of cake (crumbled).
Top with whipped topping and garnish.
Chill.

title: souffle sandwiches(servings:  6)
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter both sides of bread; place in proper size pan deep enough to hold milk.
Top with can of toppings.
Place another piece of buttered bread on top of each. Beat eggs together with milk and add grated cheese; pour this mixture over bread sandwiches.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This can be prepared a day ahead and refrigerated.
After baking, one can garnish with a few asparagus tips or a little mushroom gravy, depending on the choice of filling.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake cornbread by box instructions.
Set aside.
Saute green peppers and onions in 1 stick oleo over low heat.
Mix with rest of ingredients including crumbled corn bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Blend soups, tomatoes and onion. In a casserole dish sprayed with Pam, layer crushed chips, chicken and soup mixture (3 layers).
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 325° until brown, in 2 unbaked pie shells.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream crisco, whip in the sugar and add eggs.
Alternate the flour, milk, and flavoring.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Roll into balls about the size of a quarter, then roll in confectioners sugar to coat.

title: indian bread
directions: Mix milk, 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt, then add enough flour to make soft dough.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and eat while still hot (or can dip "sticks" into warm honey or syrup as you eat).

title: caramels
directions: Boil all together except the nuts and 1 cup cream.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add the second cup of cream and boil to a firm ball stage (248°).
Add nuts and pour without stirring into well buttered pan.
When cold, cut in squares.
Wrap each square in waxed paper.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and ice water.
Add Miracle Whip, onion, horseradish, corned beef, celery and eggs.
Place corned beef and mix into jello.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onions and ground beef, then mix all ingredients.
Place into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter until caramel color; add milk until milk is almost scalded.
Cool.
Beat eggs, add salt, sugar and vanilla. Pour into pie shell.
Grate nutmeg on top of pie.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix dressings and cheese.
Add to other ingredients.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together tomato soup, water or wine and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning if desired.
Coleslaw is a nice winter accompaniment or serve fresh tomatoes on a bed of lettuce in summer.
Serves 8.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Make Ahead.
Make the honey-mustard sauce ahead of time as directed in Step 1.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Store in an airtight container for up to 1 week.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Can double recipe.
Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Press into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs. Mix at medium speed for 5 minutes. Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spinach bread
directions: Melt margarine; saute mushrooms until wilted and add cheese until melted.
Split French bread; spread with cheese mixture. Top with pepperoni (or sausage).
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Dip eggplant slices in egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown eggplant slices in olive oil, then cover and simmer briefly until tender in a 15 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex or Corning Ware dish.
Arrange eggplant slices.
Top with spaghetti sauce, then Mozzarella cheese, then Romano cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheeses.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in one-cup measure.
Microwave on High until melted (45 seconds).
Trim and cut broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Arrange cauliflower around the outer edge of 10-inch platter, then a row of broccoli flowerets.
Fill center with slices of zucchini.
(Can use mushrooms also.)
Cover entirely with plastic wrap and seal.
Microwave on High 9 minutes. Drain liquid.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer, except nuts.
Add nuts last.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Saute the onion in the margarine.
Then add George Washington powder, eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in large, greased casserole.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour mixture into 1 gallon electric ice cream freezer and freeze according to manufactures instructions, about 35 to 40 minutes. Freeze until firm. Freeze any leftovers immediately. Yield about 1 gallon.

title: fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and cocoa or chocolate into saucepan.
Stir and boil until it makes a soft ball when tested in cold water. Take from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Stir until creamy.
Pour on buttered plate and cut into squares.
May be changed by omitting cocoa or chocolate and adding peanut butter with the butter and vanilla.
Also may add a teaspoon of peanut butter with the butter and vanilla in the chocolate mixture, making it creamier and a deliciously different flavor.

title: sloppy joes(diabetic recipe)
directions: Add salt to meat.
Turn into a large, dry, cold frying pan. Stir over medium heat with a large kitchen fork (not a spoon) until meat changes color all over, pouring off any liquid fat is it collects.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Stir and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Combine all remaining ingredients; add to meat and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn heat low; let simmer exactly for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently, until cooked and well mixed.
Makes 6 servings.
One-half cup equals 2 meat and 1 vegetable.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix, then put in a greased and floured pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl and serve with your favorite tortilla chips. A healthy snack and great for when the gang's over to watch the game!

title: spanish peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in.
Add peanuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in water, then sugar.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 2 teaspoons for each cup of hot water.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
The peach pie filling keeps fruit from turning brown.
