title: earl's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cool.
Use drinking straw (or similar size) to punch holes all over surface.
Mix together cream of coconut and milk.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, spread Cool Whip over cake, then sprinkle coconut on top.
Serve.

title: cooked potato salad dressing
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Add eggs.
Add milk and vinegar. Cook until thick.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Mix all with mayonnaise to thick consistency.
Spread on party rye.
Broil about 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: mock butter
directions: Have oleo real soft, add buttermilk, oil and salt.
Mix with mixer first on slow, then on medium until fluffy.
Refrigerate. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: best cornbread and meat recipe
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, soda, jalapeno peppers, milk, salt, salad oil and bell peppers together.
Pour half of mixture into a large greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook ground meat until all pink is gone and drain.
Mix cream-style corn, onion and grated Velveeta cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over the 1/2 mixture in pan.
Pour remainder of batter over this and bake at 375° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cooked squash until tender; drain.
Add onion, soup, sour cream and stuffing.
Mix well, then add melted margarine; mix again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chilled tortellini salad
directions: In covered blender, combine first 5 ingredients, blend until smooth.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat soda into molasses mixture until light and foamy.
Add hot water and mix well.

title: liz's rolls
directions: Place shortening, salt and sugar into bowl; add water.
Stir well.
Stir in egg and yeast; add flour all at once.
Beat with fork to make soft dough.
Cover in a bowl; let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out and put in pan and butter the top.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or brown.
Yields about 20.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Place all in mixer and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown meat slightly and drain off fat.
Add onions and cook until onions are soft.
Add water and the rest of the ingredients. Simmer 2 hours or until serving consistency.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in large container.
To serve, mix 1/3 cup hot chocolate mix to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour, corn, butter, milk and seasonings.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Bake 45 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: In heavy pan, combine sugars, corn syrup, water and salt. Cook and stir until sugars dissolve.
Cook to a boil.
Stir in margarine; cook to soft crack stage.
Add peanuts and stir. Continue to cook until hard crack stage; remove from heat. Quickly add the soda, mixing well.
Pour into greased or buttered pans.
When cool, break into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: favorite goulash
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in large pan until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in noodles, celery, catsup, salt, pepper, mushrooms (with liquid), tomatoes, green beans (with liquid) and corn (with liquid).
Add 1 cup water.
Cover; simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: country pork chops
directions: Lightly grease bottom of large skillet and brown chops. Season with
salt	and
pepper.
Place
carrots
and celery in bottom of 2-quart
casserole.
Arrange
chops
on
top.
Pour excess fat from skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and blend and pour over meat.
Cover
and
bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: orange pineapple dessert
directions: Bring juice, water and gelatin to a boil, being careful not to scorch.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Sprinkle garlic powder or salt generously over meat.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook
raisins
with
sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Remove
from heat, then add vanilla.
Set aside. Mix eggs, sugar and Crisco until creamy.
Add flour, a little at a time. Add
soda
and salt.
Dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoon and put
1 teaspoon raisins on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 8 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and milk together.
Pour over margarine.
Pour slices peaches over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Mix onion salt and water.
Sprinkle on water, a tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with work.
Work dough into a firm ball with your hands.

title: cranberry salad
directions: To cranberries, add sugar and let stand for 2 hours.
Fix strawberry jello like on the box.
Pour over berries.
Mix good. Add crushed pineapple, chopped nuts and mini marshmallows.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Combine rice, sauteed vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg; add melted butter.
Combine with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Fold in cherries.
Drop by small teaspoon into 1 1/2 or 2 inches of hot fat.
Fry 2 or more minutes until brown.
Drain and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Grease pan.
Pour in nuts and spread.
Spoon flour mixture over nuts, then layer fruit over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour cranberry meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into bite size meatballs.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes.
In separate bowl, cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add oat mixture.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into greased pan; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spoonbread casserole
directions: Mix butter and Jiffy mix.
Add both corns, sour cream, and slightly beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add the egg and molasses and blend. Sift the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture.
Blend well. Roll mixture into balls.
Put balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Open chestnuts and drain all water off; place on a paper towel to drain excess moisture.

Cut bacon slices in half and wrap 1/2 bacon strip around each chestnut and secure with round toothpicks. Place on broiler rack with 1 cup water in bottom of broiler pan (this keeps down grease splatters); broil until bacon is crisp, turning frequently to keep from burning.
Placed bacon wrapped chestnuts in large baking dish, side by side, and prepare the sauce as follows:
Empty catsup in a small saucepan.
Add sugar and soy sauce; bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 5 minutes, then pour over chestnuts in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes; remove and serve.
May be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated, then heat and serve. Serves approximately 8 to 10 people.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place skinless chicken in pan.
Mix ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Bring to a boil in covered pan.
Turn down on simmer and cook 45 minutes.
Take chicken out.
Continue cooking sauce down if desired.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Combine eggs, dry mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk together.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan layer:
bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour on egg mixture.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over egg mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bean and lamb stew(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Heat the oil and fry the onion until transparent. Toss the lamb in flour and add to the casserole. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the beans and water; stir in the tomato pure, cumin, bay leaf and rosemary. Cover; boil for 10 minutes, then simmer for 1 hour. Place the tomatoes (cut side up) on top; season. Replace the lid and cook gently for 20 minutes. Sprinkle the green onions over the top and serve.

title: orange-glazed chicken
directions: *Vegetables can be left out or use green garden peas (frozen, 1 cup) and carrots cut into thin rounds.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Cream shortening with sugar until well blended.
Add whole egg and 2 egg yolks; blend well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over the top the nuts, chips and marshmallows in that order.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually beat in brown sugar until stiff.
Spread over batter. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt and pepper in large Dutch oven. Cook over medium heat until meat is brown, stirring to crumble. Drain. Add potatoes and water to meat. Cover and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: wisconsin potato salad
directions: Cook washed, unpared potatoes in salted water until tender. Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl with a fork, beat together the vinegar, corn oil, sugar, salt and pepper; set aside but beat together again just before using.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together the day you are going to use it.

title: meatball chowder
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix thoroughly. Form into meatballs about the size of a walnut.
Makes about 40 meatballs. Dip in flour.
Heat oil in 8 to 10-quart kettle.
Lightly brown meatballs on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients (except corn, which should be added at last 10 minutes of cooking).
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and cook at slow boil for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 to 7 quarts.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
Mix cake mix, eggs, applesauce and water.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Grease Bundt pan (no flour); sprinkle part of sugar and cinnamon in bottom of pan.
Add half of cake mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of sugar and cinnamon over this.
Add remaining cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kolacky
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla. Combine flour and salt.
Add in fourths to butter mixture, blending well after each addition.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thickness on a floured surface. Cut out 2 inch circles or other shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Make a thumbprint about 1/4-inch deep in each cookie.
Fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until delicately brown on edges.

title: awesome brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
In a small bowl combine flour, b.soda, salt and set aside.
In a 2 quart sauce pan combine sugar and butter and water - bring just to a boil.
Take off burner.
Add morsels and vanilla - stir until morsels are melted.
Add eggs to pan one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture mix.
Add nuts (opt).
Spread into greased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 -35 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: chocolate-sour cream cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and soda in a large bowl; mix well and set
aside.
Combine
water,
butter and cocoa in a heavy saucepan;
bring
to
a
boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir
hot mixture into flour mixture; stir well.
Stir in eggs and sour cream;

Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.	Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Frost
with Chocolate-Peanut Butter Frosting.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken.
Take it off bone and grind it up.
Add chopped up celery, onion and eggs.
Add cheese and relish.
Mix well.
Add Miracle Whip and mix well.
Chill for 2 hours or more.
Good on bread, buns, toast, crackers, celery sticks and more.

title: potato candies
directions: Mash potatoes with sugar.
Work in coconut, vanilla and salt. Press into a shallow baking pan.
In a microwave-safe bowl, microwave chocolate on High until just melted (about 2 minutes). Stir and pour evenly over potato mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.
(Like Mounds Bars.)

title: nonnie's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add jams and preserves to mixture.
Sprinkle flour over nuts and raisins and add to mixture.
Gradually add flour and milk (put soda in cup of milk).
Mix cocoa in warm water, making a paste.
Add to mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon water to mixture.
Cook at 325° until done.
Ice with Fudge Icing.

title: marinara sauce or spaghetti sauce
directions: Puree tomatoes with juice in blender.
Add onion, tomato sauce, tomato paste, garlic, water, basil, sugar, bay leaves, oregano, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Discard bay leaves.
Serve hot over pasta. Add 1 pound browned hamburger for meat sauce.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix well and decorate with peppers.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple. Refrigerate until thickened.
Soften cream cheese; whip with fork or beaters.
Add pineapple-jello mixture, nuts and desired amount of maraschino cherries.
Pour into mold.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Slice celery very thin, cut zucchini into matchsticks, dice tomatoes and slice mushrooms.
Simmer broth, water, mushrooms, celery, thyme and pepper (10 to 15 minutes).
Add pasta and zucchini; cook, uncovered, on medium heat (6 to 7 minutes).
Add tomato, parsley and salt.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.

title: wheat germ muffins
directions: Beat together wet ingredients and sugar.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Mix into egg mixture.
Stir in the wheat germ. Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cheesy chili
directions: Brown meat with onion in a 4-quart Dutch oven or saucepot on medium-high.
Drain.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, tomato paste, water, chili powder and cumin.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until heated.
Stir in process cheese until melted. Spoon over cooked macaroni.
Top with sour cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In large bowl, soften yeast in water.
Add salt and sugar. Mix in flour and knead to make a soft, smooth dough.
Do not let rise.
Cut into long thin pieces and make into pretzel shape.
Put on cookie sheet covered with foil and dusted with flour.
Brush pretzels with beaten egg and cover with coarse salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until light brown.

title: chocolate peanut cookies
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar beating at low speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda.
Add to creamed mixture beating well.
Stir in peanuts.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Grate together cabbage, onion, bell pepper and carrots; set aside.
Combine sugar, salad oil, vinegar, salt, dry mustard and celery salt or seed.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture while still hot.
Cover and chill overnight.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Place in freeze for at least 2 hours.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes 45 minutes before using.
Mix everything.
Place in 9-inch round casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a 9 x 12-inch pan when recipe is doubled.

title: creamy taco salad
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and lettuce.
Top with cheese and serve on lettuce with chips.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Double recipe for 9-inch glass pie dish or use thin frozen pie crust for single recipe.

title: herbed pasta alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat; add green onions and garlic.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Add flour and stir well. Gradually add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheeses and herbs.
Serve over macaroni. Garnish with green onion strips.
Serves 6.

title: pork chops liegeoise
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet and add the chops.
Brown on one side, about 10 minutes.
Turn until cooked through.
Preheat the broiler.
As the chops cook, blend the cheese, cream, mustard, garlic, chives and egg yolk.
When the chops are cooked, smear mixture on one side of chops, smoothing it over.
Broil chops, cheese side up, until browned and nicely glazed.
Pour off fat from skillet.
Add the wine and water, stirring to dissolve brown particles that cling to the bottom of skillet.
Pour the hot sauce over the chops and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash strawberries.
Slice in half lengthwise or cut large berries in quarters.
Measure 4 cups berries into large saucepan 15 minutes.
Add sugar.
Mix well and heat to a full rolling boil. Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit pectin.
Stir and skim alternately 5 minutes to cool slightly and prevent floating fruit.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Makes about seven 1/2-pints.

title: stuffed chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine stuffing, oysters and broccoli.
Mix well and spread in dish.
Season chicken with salt, Accent and pepper.
Place chicken on top of stuffing. Combine oil and enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Pour over stuffing; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat vegetable oil in 10-inch ovenproof skillet or 8 or 9-inch square baking pan in oven for 3 minutes. Tilt skillet to coat bottom evenly.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
Mix until blended.
Add melted shortening.
Mix well.
Pour into hot skillet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Can be molded with wax paper into a large cheese ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken ala king
directions: In sauce pan, saute mushrooms in butter. Add salt, pepper and flour. Stir till smooth. Gradually add broth and cream, stirring constantly until thick. Add chicken and pimentos. Heat well.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat the egg yolks and add the flour, salt and pepper. Add the corn and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites. Drop small spoonfuls on greased griddle or frying pan. DO NOT COOK TOO FAST!

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Pour oil and milk in a measuring cup.
Do not stir.
Pour in dry ingredients and stir with fork until mixture cleans sides of the bowl. Smooth by kneading dough 10 times.
With dough on wax paper, press out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with unfloured biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix and bake in greased cookie sheet. Cut and put on paper towel to cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package. Mix spaghetti with soup and broth. Add chicken, peas and cheese. Save some cheese to sprinkle on top or if you prefer, use some additional cheese for topping. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chiles rellenos(deep-fried)
directions: Stuff chiles with cheese.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Mix baking powder and flour and add to beaten egg whites, 1 teaspoon at a time, beating constantly.
Beat yolks and add to the egg-flour mixture, still beating.
Dip each stuffed chile into the mixture and deep fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until separated.
Add soup and water.
Add rice and cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and noodles. Mix together.
Put in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (about 20 minutes).

title: uncooked fruitcake
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
Cut cherries in half and dates in fourths.
Mix crumbs with all the ingredients except milk.
After all pieces are well coated with crumbs, add milk and mix well.
Pack into pan lined with plastic and refrigerate for 24 hours before cutting (you may wet hands to pack).
White grape juice may be added for more moisture.
Very easy and tasty!

title: "whipped cream" icing
directions: Heat canned milk until it comes to a boil; remove from heat immediately.
Let cool.
Meanwhile, beat shortening with rotary beater until creamy.
Beat in sugar slowly until creamy and fluffy.
When milk is slightly warmer and lukewarm, pour into sugar mixture slowly while beating, add vanilla and continue beating until consistency of whipped cream, about 1 minute.
This icing tastes almost like whipped cream, is not sticky and stays soft for days.
This amount is sufficient to ice top of 7 x 11-inch sheet cake.
Double recipe to ice top and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Cover tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix well and serve keep well for days in refrigerator.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine water, sugar and cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Combine sugar, syrup, fruit juices and ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Yields 3 3/4 quarts.

title: hot cran-apple glogg
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large boiler or Dutch oven. Let stand until sugar dissolves, stirring often.
Add spices to mixture and cook over low heat until just hot.
Serve with orange slices as garnish.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix
shortening,

water
(minus 2 tablespoons), sugar and
salt.	Heat
until tepid.
Mix yeast, 2 tablespoons water, beaten
eggs
and
flour.
Mix

and knead 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let
rise
to double bulk.	Knead 10 minutes*.
Roll out on board in round shape, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in pie shape pieces.
Brush with

and roll each, starting at large end.
Place	1 inch apart on baking sheet.
Brush with butter. When double in bulk, bake at 375°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In saucepan, cook chicken, vegetables, celery and onions until tender.
Place in 3-quart oblong baking dish, saving 1 cup of liquid.
Mix soup and liquid in saucepan, adding milk until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.
Open biscuits and cut each biscuit into quarters.
Arrange biscuit pieces on hot chicken and vegetables and bake until biscuits are golden brown.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn in large pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in 5 or 6-quart container.
Bring to a boil, then add cream of tartar. Boil until gum ball stage.
Remove from stove.
Add soda, margarine and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir with long handled spoon until popcorn is coated.
Then make into balls.
Spray hands with Pam to keep from sticking.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Roll graham crackers until fine.
Combine sugar and margarine with crumbs.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with crumb mixture; press, forming crust.

title: impossible cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients (except pie filling and Streusel) 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand beater.
Pour into pie plate. Spoon pie filling over top.
Bake 25 minutes; top with Streusel. Bake until Streusel is brown, about 10 minutes longer. Cool. Refrigerate any remaining pie.

title: venison and wild rice stew
directions: Place venison, water and onions in large kettle and simmer (uncovered) for 3 hours until meat is tender.
Mix in salt, pepper and rice.
Cover kettle and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir; uncover until rice is cooked and meat absorbed.
Crusty bread desired!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients (except vanilla wafers) until well blended.
Crush vanilla wafers until fine.
Put 6 cups of vanilla wafers in mixture.
Form balls and roll in remaining crumbs.

title: batter pudding
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon of sugar, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add milk, oil and egg and beat well.
Arrange fruit in baking pan and spread mixture over fruit.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon over everything and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with potatoes.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, onion, soup, cheese and salt. Spread over potatoes.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top of cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: sugar-free rice pudding
directions: Boil rice, milk and salt for 1 hour over medium heat.
Stir often.
Rice should be well done.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and Equal.
If runny, thicken with beaten egg.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Garnish with walnuts if desired.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and then add the rest of the ingredients, except the noodles.
Pour into 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans and top each with 1/2 can of the Chinese noodles.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: horseradish dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Nice served over spinach, broccoli or asparagus.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Mix water, salt, seasoning and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Cut haddock into 3-inch squares, place in pan and boil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with melted butter.

title: mushroom risotto
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring the stock to a simmer over moderate heat.
Reduce the heat to very low and cover until ready to use.

title: babka(polish sweet bread)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in lukewarm water. Add sifted flour. Mix thoroughly and set aside to raise. In the meantime, prepare a mixture of the egg yolks, sugar, salt, butter or oleo, egg whites, lemon juice or orange juice and lemon or orange rind. Beat in mixer until smooth, then fold in the raisins. Add this mixture to the yeast mixture with 4 more cups sifted flour (or enough to make a soft dough). Knead thoroughly by hand. Put in small tube pans or form round loaf with 2 strips of dough over top to form a cross. Cover and let rise again. Brush top with egg yolks or milk. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: micro brittle
directions: Stir together salt, sugar and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole. Place in microwave on High and cook 4 minutes. Add pecans and stir well. Cook 4 minutes. Reduce this to 3 1/2 minutes if the microwave is 800 watts.

Add butter and vanilla; blend well. Return to microwave and cook 1 more minute or until light and foamy. Add soda and pour immediately onto a greased cookie sheet; cool. This must be done quickly as the brittle hardens rapidly. Break and store in airtight container.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream cake mix, sugar and oil together. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each one.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add poppy seed and mix well.
Bake in greased pans for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce. Mix well; add undrained pineapple.
Add chopped celery and nuts. Refrigerate until jelled.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Into a microwave serving dish, layer the ingredients in order given.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vidalia onions with cheese sauce
directions: Peel onions; cook in boiling salt water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Place onions in dish.
Set aside.
In top of double boiler, blend butter and flour thoroughly; add liquid gradually, stirring constantly.
Add grated cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Cover tightly and place over hot water until ready to use.
Pour over Vidalia onions.
Garnish with grated eggs, parsley and paprika.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger barley vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables and barley are tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Makes 10 (1 1/2 cups) servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add soup. Add cheese and let melt.
Mix thoroughly. Add the broccoli, cooked and drained. Add mushrooms. Heat and serve with Wheat Thins.
Can keep hot in chafing dish.

title: raisin-p-nut butter clusters
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and peanut butter together in medium size saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins and Frosted Flakes.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto buttered cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese and add chicken spread, salad dressing, celery salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix thoroughly and roll in chopped nuts. Chill.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except Bac*Os.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir in Bac*Os.
Good for raw vegetables.

title: chicken curry
directions: Fry onions in butter.
Add everything else and cook on low. Heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or pita bread.
Serves 4.

title: oriental noodle dish
directions: Add seasoning package to 2 cups boiling water.
Add shrimp, cabbage and green onions.
Cook until tender.
Add noodles.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Can use any kind of meat and add more cabbage to suit taste.

title: peachy cream pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water until smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 1-2 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat and whisk in gelatin until completely dissolved.
Add peaches and refrigerate approx. 20 minutes until slightly thickened.

title: sigara borek(turkish appetizer)
directions: Cut each phyllo sheet into 4 pieces.
Place some filling along the long side of each piece.
Fold the edge over the filling, tuck in the ends and roll like a cigarette.
Brush some water on the seam to ensure it sticks and fry in very hot oil for 5 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper, then serve hot.

title: best chicken macaroni ever!(our family's favorite)
directions: Cook your chicken in 3-inches water 2 hours.
Season your water with 2 teaspoons salt and 1 onion.
After you get the chicken all cut up, cook the macaroni, then drain it.
While still hot, add other ingredients and pats of butter.
Bake in well buttered oblong Pyrex dish, covered with foil or lid for approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven.
(Can be made a day ahead, refrigerated, then cooked.)

title: frosty golden punch
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, in blender at high speed, blend crushed pineapple with liquid, one can at a time until thick.
In punch bowl, combine blended pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Makes 20 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and flavorings.
Add dry ingredients by halves.
Pack into cookie press and form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the flour, until well blended. Add flour, pour in well-greased pans.
Make two 9-inch pies.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beans and stuff
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove.
Brown onion and green pepper in drippings.
Add to the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into 4-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole bowl. Melt the margarine. Stir in the cracker crumbs.
Spread crumb mixture over the vegetable mixture. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat eggs and egg yolks; mix in milk and add salt.
Add flour a little at a time to thicken.
Mix in enough flour to make it the consistency of very thick pudding.
Let rest for 15 minutes, covered.
Boil a big pot of salted water.
Drop teaspoonfuls into boiling water.
When they come to the top, let boil 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Do not overcrowd.
Do this in separate batches.
Strain dumplings; toss with butter.
This recipe yields a lot.
Can be reduced by half.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, flour, cocoa, butter, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Stir until mixed (use a wire whisk).
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, using a wire whisk, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla extract and mix.
Pour into a baked and cooled pie shell.
Make meringue with egg whites, bake until browned.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a little water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix chicken soup and sour cream and stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Spread half of mixture into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon in vegetable mixture; sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.
Makes two small casseroles.
One may be frozen for later use.

title: melissa's cake
directions: Mix coconut and the pecans and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Pour batter on top of pecans and coconut mixture.
In saucepan, melt cream cheese and butter.
Remove from heat; stir in box confectioners sugar and spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate and milk together.
Add rest of ingredients and put in refrigerator.
(No semi-sweet chocolate.)

title: two week slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, olives and bell pepper in a large bowl. Pour 3/4 cup sugar over mixture.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Cool and pour over cabbage mixture; mix well.
Store overnight in refrigerator before serving.
May be kept for 2 weeks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all juice from spinach.
In large bowl, mix sour cream, mayo and soup mix.
Add spinach.
(If you run through blender or food processor, texture is finer.) Refrigerate in covered bowl at least 3 hours.
Hollow out bread.
Serve dip inside.
Cut up bread in chunks.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread
into
large shallow baking dish.
Beat egg yolks; mix with
other ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve.
May make ice cubes of Kool-Aid to mix in mixture.

title: old-fashion italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Add together in 2-quart saucepan Ragu sauce, paste and puree. Cook on low heat.
Stir until paste blends in.
Add garlic powder, basil, pepper, sugar and oil.
Stir constantly until blended. Reduce heat to simmer for 3 hours.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese and noodle ring
directions: Cook onion and pimiento in butter until onion is tender (do not brown).
Combine egg, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix noodles and bread crumbs with cheese mixture.
Add onion and pimiento.
Pour into greased ring mold or loaf pan.
Set in pan of warm water and bake in moderate oven (350°) 1 hour.
Unmold and serve with creamed foods, such as chicken, fish or vegetables. Makes 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bananas, sugar and shortening; mix well.
Add the eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Grease 1 loaf pan and pour mixture in.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix together and add chicken.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Cook on the grill.
Enjoy.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Saute meat, onion and green pepper together with a little oil until brown, then stir in rice.
(I puree onion and green pepper so my boys will not see the pepper.)

title: layered dip
directions: Spread refried beans in the bottom of dish, spread cheese and jalapeno dip over beans.
Then spread avocado dip over cheese dip. Next mix sour cream and taco seasoning in small bowl and spread over avocado dip.
Sprinkle on chopped chilies and olives.
Then spread on picante sauce.
Sprinkle on chopped tomatoes, green onions, and shredded cheese.
Place in refrigerator for at least two hours to sit.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: hawaiian pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 10 minutes; let cool.
Slice eggs in half, take out the middle; mix cheese, mayo, mustard, pickles, eggs, salt and pepper.
Place mixture back in egg halves.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: mock silly putty
directions: Prepare Borax solution by adding 4 grams of Borax to 96 grams of water.
(Or you can add 1 tablespoon Borax to 1 cup water.) Measure 25 ml. of glue into paper cup.
Add 20 ml. of water and stir well.
Add 5 drops of food coloring; stir well.
Add 5 ml. Borax solution and stir.
Remove the solid material and place on a paper towel.
Pull the solid off the stirrer.
This material will be sticky for about 1 or 2 minutes.
Store in a Ziploc bag or other airtight container.

title: simple bread
directions: Measure water into large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water.
Add dry milk, sugar, salt, butter and about half the flour.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add remaining flour and knead until smooth.
Divide into 2 equal parts and form into loaves.
Place into greased bread pans and let rise until about double.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: holiday dessert pizza
directions: Press dough onto a 14-inch pizza pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until browned and puffed. Cool completely.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 2 1/2 minutes with mixer. Cook in Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 300° oven.
Do not open oven until 1 hour and 10 minutes is up.
Check with toothpick to see if cake is done.
If not, cook a few more minutes until cake is done.
Cool a few minutes, then remove from
Bundt pan on cake plate.
Ice with frosting, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water until tender.
Mix margarine with stuffing.
Put half on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain squash.
Add soup, sour cream and carrots. Put on top of stuffing in dish.
Put remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put cheese on top, if you like.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat
sugar into eggs; blend in Milnot, water, salt and vanilla.
Serve
chilled
or
warm, topped with whipped Milnot topping.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
In mixing bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips. Spread in pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all except 1/2 of noodles.
Sprinkle last 1/2 over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt white chocolate and add in peanut butter.
Pour into an 8-inch greased square pan.
Refrigerate until hardens.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Combine in bowl oil, pumpkin and eggs.
Mix well.
Add Bisquick and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler with butter.
Brown meat.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
Add cheese mixture.
Put on English muffin or bottom of hamburger bun.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. This makes 24 servings.
Good to serve at youth activities.

title: mom's granola
directions: Mix everything together, except honey, oil and raisins.
Melt honey and oil over low heat until very liquid and mixed well.
Add to dry ingredients and spread on cookie sheets.
Bake about 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
When cool, add raisins.

title: garden patch scalloped corn
directions: Saute green onions in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in corn and remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.
May be doubled.

title: pineapple and nut cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer only until all ingredients are combined.
Pour into a pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry pecan ring
directions: Blend sugar, vanilla and water.

title: wynette cook's coconut pie
directions: This recipe makes its own crust.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing flour, blending well.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until brown.

title: poppy seed orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients at low speed until moistened (1 minute).
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin tin.
Bake 17 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 1 dozen.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add tomato; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Place tomato mixture in container of an electric blender; cover and process until smooth.
Add milk and next 3 ingredients.
Process 5 seconds.
Return tomato mixture to pan and cook over medium heat 8 minutes or until heated.
Garnish with fresh oregano, if desired.
Yields 4 cups.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine in medium saucepan the cranberries, pears, sugar and lemon peel.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Skim off foam with spoon.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, until fruits are tender.
Pour into bowl and allow to cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Serve warm or cold.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Work in flour until dough holds together. Shape dough by teaspoonful into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg white.
Dip balls in egg white, then roll in pecans.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press thumb deeply into center of each. Bake 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Cool and fill thumbprint with jelly.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, pork, onion, bread crumbs, milk, salt, pepper, nutmeg, allspice and egg in large bowl; blend well.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Brown on all sides in shortening in skillet.
Remove meatballs.
Stir flour into drippings; cook until flour browns.
Add water and bouillon cubes; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add milk slowly while mixing.
Fold in frozen blueberries just prior to spooning batter into greased or paper lined tins.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 325°.

title: salmon steak with dill sauce
directions: Mix ingredients. Spoon over salmon steaks. Broil for 10 minutes or until sauce turns dark on top.

title: apple-cheese salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, except greens, and add to first mixture.
Toss well and serve on greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Cook noodles according to directions. Grate cheese, saving some for the top. Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together all other ingredients except cheese. Pour batter over butter and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: lime foam jello
directions: Drain juice from pears to make 1 cup.
Heat juice to a boil. Add Jell-O, mix and let cool.
Mix cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Add cooled pear juice mixture to cream cheese mixture. Chill slightly.
Mash pears with Cool Whip, then mix with cooled Jell-O.
Refrigerate.

title: scones
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add 3/4 cup milk and mix quickly with knife.
Add remaining milk only if necessary to mix a soft dough.

title: easy crispy chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then in cereal to coat.
Place chicken pieces on a foil-lined baking sheet.
The foil is for easy clean up.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a large saucepan cook sugar, Karo, and salt over a medium heat until small amount forms a firm ball in cold water or 245°on thermometer.
Stir constantly.
Add next ingredients gradually so mixture doesn't stop boiling.
Add butter, milk and pecans. Continue cooking until a small amount forms a firm ball in cold water.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Let stand a few minutes.
Drop on greased muffin tins or cookie sheet 1 tablespoon at a time.
Don't drop on waxed paper.

title: lawrence's sugar nuts
directions: Combine both sugars and sour cream in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until temperature reaches 238° or until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are coated.
Turn onto wax paper.
With a fork, separate the nuts. Let dry.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring lightly. Use salt when boiling.
Mix all ingredients together, except 1 egg, paprika and celery (use these for decorating top of salad).

title: canned vegetables in dutch oven
directions: Line Dutch oven with tinfoil.
Place vegetables in the oven. Cover with lid.
Bake with coals on top and bottom about 20 minutes.

title: reese's cup
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter together and shape into balls.
Melt 5 Hershey bars and 1/2 bar paraffin on low heat.
Dip balls into mixture and let cool.

title: country captain
directions: Wash and pat chicken parts with paper towel.
Sprinkle each piece with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour, mixed with paprika. Melt butter in skillet and brown chicken pieces.
Arrange chicken in an oblong dish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Mix milk with cornstarch in saucepan. Add sherry, chicken stock, pepper, salt, onion salt and nutmeg.
Heat over low heat, stirring until thickened. Simmer 5 minutes. Boil noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Mix noodles and mushrooms in sauce and add cooked chicken pieces. Turn into a baking dish and top with 3 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven until browned, about 20 minutes. Serve from casserole. Serves 6.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Put in graham cracker crust for pie.
Chill several hours.

title: thingamajigs
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
Add Velveeta cheese while still warm and let it melt into meat mixture.
Once melted, spoon onto party toast.
You may freeze and they keep for a long time. When reheating, put temperature on 350° for 10 minutes.
No need to thaw.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugars and eggs and beat well.
Add flour and seasonings (may substitute almond or lemon flavoring for vanilla).
Mix well.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, then mix in vanilla.
Pour over mixture of confectioners sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Mix quickly until smooth.

title: bagel pizza snacks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In small bowl, combine tomato paste and oregano.
Spread each bagel half with about 1 tablespoon tomato paste mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with onion and green pepper; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate mocha crazy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add liquids.
Mix 3 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: the best banana pudding
directions: Fix bananas and wafers in a bowl loosely.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over quickly.
Top with crushed wafers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and beat until smooth.
Put into a large casserole.
Top with last 4 ingredients.
Place over entire top of mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: healthy turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add Worcestershire sauce and simmer until thickened.
Add cheese, green pepper and scallions to the sauce and mix well.
Stir in turkey and spaghetti; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana date nut cookies
directions: Blend bananas, salt, vanilla and dates.
Mix all together. Drop onto sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Make graham cracker crust according to directions (double the recipe) and put crust on bottom of 9x13 cake pan. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Then mix in cool whip. Add crushed pineapple. pour this mixture over crust. Cool in refrigerator a few hours or overnight. Put pie filling on top before serving.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: Sprinkle chicken with flour and spices.
Place in skillet; saute in butter, browning.
Remove chicken.
Drain off fat, reserving 3 tablespoons.
Add onion and garlic to pan; saute until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring until marmalade melts.
Return chicken to skillet.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until tender and spoon sauce over chicken occasionally while cooking.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Prior to making, pop popcorn according to directions.
Do not salt.
(Microwave popcorn should not be used.)
Mix in medium saucepan the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and pour over popped popcorn.
Mix in large bowl until thoroughly covered. Cool.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Take off burner.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, nuts and vanilla. Stir well.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoons.
Let cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower in small pieces.
Chop or dice celery. Parboil the frozen peas only until thawed.
Combine all ingredients and leave in refrigerator overnight before serving. Will keep several days.
Toss with ripe olives and fresh tomatoes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and salad oil until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients except apples and nuts and mix well.
Add apples and nuts and mix. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer about 15 minutes, or until onion is done.
Use over chicken, steak or ribs.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Brown onion, pepper and ground beef; then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and simmer or bake in a moderate oven for one hour.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Combine other ingredients in crock-pot.
Add meat to other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 2 hours.
Cook on high for 1 hour.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes, or until bread crumbs are brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: canned sliced green tomatoes
directions: Fill with hot water and seal.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
They do not get soft.
They are delicious.
Open and drain.
Roll each slice in cornmeal and
fry.
Enjoy!

title: chicken mozzarella(weight watchers logo)
directions: Dip chicken in flour and spices.
In skillet, saute mushrooms in margarine.
When browned, remove mushrooms with slotted spoon. Put cutlets in skillet and brown.
Put chicken in baking dish (with juices from pan), top with mushrooms and shredded cheese. Broil to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Place zucchini in microwave to soften.
Let cool, cut in half. Scoop out half of zucchini pulp and set aside.
Saute zucchini pulp, onions, pepper, celery, mushrooms, tomatoes, garlic, 2 tablespoons olive oil and spices.
Add Ricotta and Cheddar cheeses. Spoon evenly into zucchini boats; top with bread crumbs.
Place in oiled pan.
Drizzle olive oil over zucchini.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: grandpa lund's egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks, gradually adding 1/2 cup of sugar until fluffy.
Beat whites until very stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar to beaten whites.
Fold whites into yolks.
Stir in milk and cream.
Add Four Roses and rum.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve very cold with grated nutmeg.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti (as much as fits in your bowl) as package directs.
Drain and wash in cold water.
Coat spaghetti with oil (keeps from sticking together).
Add next 6 ingredients. Toss.
Top with chunked tomatoes.
Add wine vinegar to taste. Cover top of bowl with McCormick Salad Supreme and add herbs and spices salad dressing to coat well.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix warm mashed potatoes with sifted sugar.
Roll out in an oblong shape and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up into jelly roll and cut in slices.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix crackers with margarine and poppy seeds.

title: ma's lentils and rice
directions: Place uncooked lentils in clean pot (not aluminum), cover with water until water is 1 1/2 to 2 inches above level of beans.
Let soak for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.
Drain lentils and return pot; fill again with water to same level as before.
Bring water to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours with cover.
Add celery, carrot, onion, tomato, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper 1/2 hour before lentils are done cooking.
Stir lentils occasionally during cooking time; add more water if necessary to keep beans covered.
When lentils are done cooking you may mix rice in all at once or individual servings.
If so desired, add a dash of olive oil to each individual serving and mix.

title: dream cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat on bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix remaining ingredients all together and spread on top of cooked mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable potato salad
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Cook potatoes.
Mix together with herbs of your choice.
Use everything fresh from the garden.

title: pink lady
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cool until cool throughout. Garnish with a few more pecans on top.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip squares
directions: Cream margarine into sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Blend. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Mix with creamed mixture. Stir in peanut butter chips. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: christmas pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs; add dry ingredients, now pumpkin.
Spread on greased and floured pan (oblong).
Top with nuts if used.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Put butter into milk and heat until butter is melted.
In a separate bowl, combine corn, flour, sugar, eggs, salt and pepper. Add milk to the substance.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old shortbread
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and sugar; mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Poke holes with fork once mix is in pan.
Heat the first 3 minutes on bottom rack of oven, then for 1 hour, in slow 275° oven.
Cut into squares as soon as out of oven.

title: beans and rice
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 1-quart microwavable bowl. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until heated.
Stir in 1/4 cup bacon crumbs.
Top with remaining bacon.
Garnish with green onions, if desired.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Prepare roux with butter and flour.

Add milk. Stir until very thick. Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. In another pan, heat wine, stocks, mushrooms, crabmeat and diced boiled shrimp. Add to thick sauce mixture and simmer. Serves 6 generously.

title: crepes fitzgerald(servings:  6)
directions: Inside each crepe, put reasonable amount of both cream cheese and sour cream.
Roll each crepe into a tubular shape.
In a chafing dish, melt butter over medium heat.
Mix in strawberries and sugar until sauce thickens.
Add strawberry liqueur.
Cook until sauce continues to thicken, then flambe with brandy and mix gently.
Spoon strawberry mixture over crepes.
Serve.
Suggested Wine: Moet and Chandon White Star.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and margarine together.
Add cocoa, vanilla and milk; mix well.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into margarine mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes.
Serves 36; 1 cookie per serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Use half of cheeses for mixture and half for top.
Combine ingredients of your choice and fill tortillas.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Place remaining cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix the milk, sugar and cream cheese together until smooth. Add the Cool Whip.
Mix well. Cut angel food cake into thin slices.
Place half of these in oblong pan.
Pour half of the topping over the cake.
Place the other half of the cake on top of this.
Pour remaining topping.
Place cherry pie filling on last.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.
Eat with rice or bread.

title: onion casserole
directions: Put sliced onions on bottom of a 12 x 7-inch casserole.
Add layer of crushed crackers, sausage, then another layer of onions. Spread soup on top of onions and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Add the cheese and pimentos, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spectacular spinach
directions: Get as much water as possible out of spinach.
Set aside. Gradually heat milk in saucepan and add mustard, garlic and red pepper.
Saute onion in 1 tbsp. butter until onion is tender and clear.
Add to milk mixture.
Make a light brown roux with the melted butter and flour over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Cut the cheese into cubes and add to roux.
Stir until melted.
Add milk mixture and stir until smooth.
Cool for 10-15 minutes.
Add spinach.
Stir.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Salt to taste.
Place in 350° oven until bubbling and cheese is melted (about 20 minutes).
Leftovers (if any) can be frozen or used for dip.

title: mrs. richard's chocolate cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the egg and melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add the sour milk and flour alternately, beginning with the milk.

title: crusty potato tidbits
directions: Scrub potatoes; quarter.
Place in saucepan with 1/2 inch boiling, salted water.
Cover and bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until tender.
Peel potatoes; mash with milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese and onion; mix well.
Shape mixture in balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Dip potato balls into beaten eggs, then roll in crushed cornflakes.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until balls are hot and crusty.
Makes about 70 appetizer balls.

title: quick and easy custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar on high speed with mixer until thickened, then add vanilla, nutmeg and salt. Beat until blended. Gradually stir in hot milk, stirring constantly. Pour in pastry shell. Bake on lower oven rack at 400° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in plastic bowl with cover on. Shake well. Add cold water; shake well.
Put on floured board.
Makes 2 crusts.
Never fail.

title: baked beans
directions: In 2-quart dish, put bacon and microwave on High for about 3 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Remove bacon. Crumble and set aside. Reserve bacon drippings in same dish. In same dish, add onion and celery to bacon drippings.

Microwave on High 3 minutes, uncovered. Add crumbled bacon, green pepper, beans, mustard, ketchup, brown sugar, Tabasco sauce, liquid smoke and water. Microwave on High 5 minutes, then on 70% power for 15 minutes, uncovered, until thick.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: cherry smoothie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 3 tablespoon of syrup.
Combine cherries, reserved syrup and yogurt in blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes one at a time; blend until smooth. Serve in tall glasses with straws.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: cherry-lious salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate to chill. Stir before serving.

title: rum nut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Beat butter until light.
Gradually add sugars and continue beating until very light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine rum, milk and vanilla.
Add to batter, alternating with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 20 servings.

title: divinity
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Cook to hard-crack stage.
Pour slowly into egg whites beaten with cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: soft caramels
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 15 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Cook bacon; remove from pan and drain grease, but leave enough to saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans and bacon.
Simmer 5 minutes; add beans and bacon. Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for total of 30 minutes.
After first 15 minutes, sprinkle top with paprika.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Place in microwave-safe dish.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add butter and salt to taste.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix really good the first 6 ingredients.
Brush oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1 sheet of filo; brush with oleo.
Do that about 7 or 8 layers.
Put filling on that and add about 7 more sheets of filo, brushing after each with oleo.
Put in refrigerator to chill, then cut through top layer just before you bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Heat mincemeat and milk to boiling in 3-quart saucepan (stir frequently); reduce heat.
Simmer until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough in 1 rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes, at 375°.

title: pretzel chicken
directions: Soak chicken in salt water.
Remove skin.
Beat eggs and milk. Dredge chicken in egg-milk mixture.
Coat with mashed pretzels. Place in frypan or baking dish with oil or non-greasy spray.
If frypan is used, cover with lid.
If oven dish is used, cover with foil for 30 minutes to cook chicken.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover for the last 30 minutes to brown.

title: cherry salad
directions: Put cherry pie filling and sugar in pan and boil 2 minutes. Stir often.
Take off stove.
Add Jell-O.
Mix real good.
Stir in pineapple.
When cool enough, put in refrigerator to jell.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: ants on a log
directions: Put the peanut butter on the celery in the hole; put raisins on. You now have ants on a log.

title: grandma c.'s bread pudding
directions: * These are optional, but almost a must.
Sprinkle raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon over top if used.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add 2 cups fresh strawberries (unsweetened).
Pour in baked or graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: sangria
directions: Combine the fruit and 1/4 cup sugar in a large pitcher.
Pour in wine and brandy and stir until well mixed.
Taste and add up to 1/4 cup more sugar if you prefer it sweeter.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until thoroughly chilled.

Just before serving, pour in chilled club soda to taste, adding up to 24 ounces of the soda. Stir again and serve at once in chilled wine glasses or glasses may be filled with ice before adding Sangria.

title: kooky salad
directions: Cook peas 7 minutes.
Layer in oblong pan (preferably glass) in order given.
Then spread with 1/2 pint real mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil; do not use Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Divide filling between two unbaked pie shells.
Top with pecans.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth. Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spoon the pie filling into the cake, in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and cake tests done.
Filling will sink into the cake while baking.
To serve, cut into 16 pieces.
Place bottom side up on serving plate. Dust with powdered sugar, if used.
Spoon lightly sweetened whipped cream over each serving, if desired.

title: german sauerkraut dish
directions: Combine potatoes, sauerkraut, soup, salt. pepper and cream. Mix well and pour into bottom of buttered 9x13 pan. Lay sausage over top and press down slightly into potato mixture. Sprinkle with paprika if desired. Bake at 350 degrees for 75 minutes.

title: no egg cake
directions: Mix all together.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in sheet cake
pan.
Can use powdered sugar icing. Pour on cake while warm.
You can also add nuts if desired.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Beat Jeremiah until frothy.
Add Judges.
Combine with the creamed mixture and beat thoroughly.
Sift half of 1 Kings together with Amos.
Add rest of 1 Kings.
Combine first mixture with second mixture.
Chop 1 Samuel 30:12 and Nahum; flour these before adding to mixture. 2 Chronicles is added last.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1 jelly roll pan with Pam for 2 seconds.
In large bowl, toss chicken with milk.
Mix crumbs, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces and place in prepared pan.
Spray pieces with Pam for a total of 15 seconds.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mushroom stew
directions: Soak dried mushrooms in 1 cup hot water.
Cook leeks in butter for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, liquid they soaked in, wine and cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Uncover, cook 15 minutes more, until liquid is reduced.
Add Madeira and Port, cook another 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and either sherry or wine vinegar right before serving.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Boil for 5 minutes, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon soda.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Mix well. Pour over the Crispix cereal in a large bowl; coat well.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: aunt jane's lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter, then beat in the eggs one at a time.
Sift the flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with the milk, then add extract.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan greased and floured.
Place in cold oven.
Heat oven to 350° as cake bakes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door during baking.
Cook cake in pan, then invert on a plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lumpia fried(phillippine egg roll)
directions: In 3 tablespoons hot oil, brown garlic.
Add onions, then pork.
Cook 5 minutes on high heat, then add shrimp.
Reduce heat, season with salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in green beans, cook for 1 minute, then add cabbage, sweet potato, soy sauce and m.s.g.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Cool.

title: cucumber and tarragon
directions: In a bowl, mix vinegar with water.
Slice a cucumber and place it in the bowl with the vinegar.
Add several sprigs of tarragon (or Tagetes Lucida), layering it with the cucumber slices and refrigerate for several hours.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Prepare lettuce.
Blend remaining ingredients for dressing.

title: mama king's macaroni & cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done, drain. While still hot, add butter and all but 1/2 cup cheese. Mix well. Beat eggs & add to macaroni mixture. Add milk & seasonings. Mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish & sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake in 350 degree oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in buttered baking dish; top with 1/2 cup buttered corn bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly blend cheeses.
Fold in remainder of ingredients, except for the nuts.
Cover and refrigerate.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: doughnut holes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients to form batter.
Heat oil for frying in medium size skillet.
Drop batter by teaspoons into hot oil. Remove when brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: decorator buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening together with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in sugar, 1 cup at a time, blending well after each addition.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often with a spatula.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy. Keep icing covered with lid or damp cloth and store in refrigerator when not in use.
Yields 3 cups.

title: bob's frog more stew
directions: You also need 10 to 12-quart stockpot.

title: crawfish pie
directions: *Suggest that you use already prepared pie crust in the refrigerated food section of the grocery store.

title: waldorf cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add chocolate and eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in 3 layer pans and bake at 350° until done.
Let cool before icing.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together first three ingredients with sugar.
Add water, stirring until dissolved.
Add all juices and peppermint sticks. Serve over ice.
Add orange slices.

title: make-ahead muffin mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine oatmeal and boiling water; mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine egg whites (may use 4 whole eggs), oil, sugar, salt and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Combine flour and soda; mix well. Add wheat bran and mix well.
Add liquid ingredients to the oatmeal mixture and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix until just moistened. Do not overmix!
Store, tightly covered, in the refrigerator.
It will keep for up to a month.
Makes 12 cups.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Whip the Dream Whip according to box directions.
Whip the cream cheese into the Dream Whip.
Stir in the powdered sugar. Put the cream mixture on the cooled crust and cover with the cherry pie filling.
(Fill the can of cherries all the way to the top with water and stir to make the filling thinner.)
Chill.

title: christmas dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water in large bowl.
Add oil, honey, salt and hot water; mix well.
Gradually add flour; will be sticky, but do not knead.
Chill overnight.
Shape rolls and place in greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: sneaky pete's(alcoholic drink)
directions: Stir all ingredients together and freeze.
Serve frozen!

title: sliced baked potatoes(how to microwave)
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a microwave-safe dish or pan. Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.

title: orange julius
directions: Put into blender and blend.
Put one ice cube in at a time and blend until cube is crushed.
Proceed until all 7 cubes are crushed.
Serve in tall glasses.
Makes 2 glasses.
Drink slowly and enjoy!

title: jack's favorite pie
directions: Grind or chop raisins and cranberries.
Put filling ingredients, except vanilla, into a saucepan.
Cook over low heat about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and let cool. Pour filling into pastry lined pie plate; cover with top crust or lattice crust.
Make slits or air vents in top crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes, until browned.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
This filling is on the tart side.
Taste the filling and add 1/4 more sugar if it is too tart.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook hen
or fryers with salt and pepper.
Simmer until the meat falls
off the bones; remove bones.
Cut meat in bite size pieces.
In
large
container
mix
meat
with
cream
of mushroom soup,
cream
of chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
In
small
amount
of broth, simmer onions and pepper until
tender.
Add
to
chicken mixture.
Line a large baking dish with 6 tortillas.
Pour 1/2 of chicken mixture and top with 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese.
Repeat, topping with last 1/2 pound cheese.
Bake
in
350° oven until cheese melts and starts to brown.
Serve
with
slaw,
pinto beans and Mexican cornbread.

title: punch(beverage)
directions: Make ice ring containing pineapple chunks and cherries. Freeze.
Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and ice ring.
Serves approximately 50.

title: broccoli and red pepper sauté
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat and cook broccoli, bell pepper, onion and garlic about 5 minutes or until onion is tender,
stirring occasionally. Combine soup mix with water; add to vegetable mixture. Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender. Sprinkle with almonds and serve.

title: broccoli, carrot and snow pea slaw
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Add the broccoli, carrots and snow peas and blanch for 30 seconds.
Drain, refresh under cold running water and drain again.
Place in a large bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and toss to coat.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges, peel side down, in 2 shallow baking pans.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Brush occasionally with mixture.
Serves 8.

title: presbyterian rock cookies
directions: Make dough stiff enough to drop off spoon.

title: old fashioned split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in chicken broth and water overnight.
Place peas and soaking liquid, ham hock, onion, celery, carrots, garlic, bay leaves, and salt in slow cooker.
Cook on low for 8 hours. Remove onion and bay leaves, and discard.
Remove ham hock, and dice meat.
Can add 1/2 c. heavy cream, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Boil together dates, prunes and raisins in water until soft. Add oleo (set aside).
Mix together eggs, soda, salt, flour and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Mix together and put in a greased 7 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You can also add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon if desired.
(I double this.)

title: chicken-ziti salad
directions: Cook ziti.
Cook beans 1 minute.
Add zucchini and cook 2 minutes longer.
Vegetables should be crunchy.
Drain and allow to cool.
Mix with ziti.
Add cucumber, chicken and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold in mayonnaise and dill.
Refrigerate until used.
If dressing becomes too stiff, mix in more consomme.

title: maupin and rader bacon cure(circa 1924)
directions: Mix dry, then rub on. Use about half rubbed in.
Let stand a week, then rub on remainder.
Let stand another week.
Rub the third time and let stand until all is thoroughly absorbed. Just the black pepper will show.
Hang and smoke.
Use green alder. When half done, use a little green myrtle wood (native to Oregon) part of the day only, for a delightful flavor.
Don't overdo!
Too much will make bacon and hams bitter.
Finish smoking process with green alder.
This is a very old recipe.
Best ever.

title: smoky ground beef cakes
directions: Combine ground beef with the egg, onion, salt, pepper, sage and liquid smoke; then shape into 6 thick cakes.

title: peanut butter dressing
directions: In small saucepan, combine peanut butter, oil and red pepper. Heat, stirring constantly, until the consistency of smooth paste; remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and serve over green salad.
Two 1/4 teaspoons equal 1 fat.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Butter pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Heat until boils (do not stir). Cook until liquid starts to brown.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: corn and vidalia onion casserole
