directions: Saute green peppers and onions in margarine.
Add corn, pimentos and eggs.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm.
(Optional:
may top with French fried onions or cracker crumbs.)

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients in order given.
Then mix mayonnaise and sugar thoroughly.
Spread on top of layered vegetables.
Then sprinkle cheese and finally the bacon pieces.
Refrigerate at least several hours before serving.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Chop chicken breasts and mix all ingredients together and put in a greased casserole dish. Crush crackers and top casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until crackers on top turn a golden brown.

title: pan preparation
directions: Mix and keep refrigerated.
Apply to pans with a pastry brush.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix ingredients (except sausage) and cook over low heat until thickened.
Add sausage and chunk pineapple and juice.
Simmer for at least 1/2 hour.

title: grandma bea's french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, cream, flour and vanilla alternately.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepper relish
directions: Add peppers and onions; cook 20 minutes, then can.
Could add 4 to 5 medium hot peppers if you want hot relish.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 stick melted margarine and beaten egg. Press in the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and put back in oven until marshmallows are melted.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with syrup.
Add peanut butter chips and heat until melted.
(I use my microwave for this.)
Stir in nuts and cereal.
Spread on top of marshmallows. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass dish.
Microwave 5 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle extra chips or Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: hot wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings.
Discard last joint. Deep fry wings. Melt butter in hot sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Dip wings in hot sauce mix. Enjoy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap chestnuts in bacon.
Secure with tooth picks.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small sauce pan.
Heat for 45 seconds to blend.
pour over water chestnuts and refrigerate over night. Place on cooking grill, cover with paper towels, and cook 6 minutes.
Remove the crisp ones.
Continue cooking at 2 minute intervals, removing
the crisp ones until all are crisp.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans pieces.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies (they will look light and moist; do not overbake) 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 375°.
Bake until tender.

title: pasa de shuto
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and beef; drain fat.
Add vegetables and saute just until crisp-tender.
Stir in soups, tomato sauce, and spices.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Add to skillet and stir gently to mix. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: butter-caramel cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk and sifted dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture. Add vanilla.
Mix well
Pour into four 8-inch
layer pans or three 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cut chicken into fairly large pieces.
Starting with chicken, layer chicken, celery and bread crumbs in a buttered casserole. Beat eggs and add to the broth with salt and pour over the mixture.
Use a fork to get broth through the mixture.
Put a small amount of bread crumbs on top, parsley and butter (cut up in small pieces).
Bake in 350°
oven for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean
when pushed into mixture.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mash eggplant and tomatoes, then add onion and eggs.
Stir until it looks like scrambled eggs.
Stir in cheese.
Add 3/4 cup of bread crumbs.
Pour into baking dish.
Add rest of bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut up the apples.
Mix together with the brown sugar.
Cover bottom of a shallow pan or casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients until fine.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until golden brown.
It is important that the oven be slow.
This tastes caramely and is very delicious.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream egg yolks, sugar and flour; add milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Add coconut, vanilla and oleo.
Pour into pie crust.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into well oiled baking dish. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees for glass baking dish 13 x 9 inches.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
I press to form a crust.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, then coconut and nuts.
Top with sweetened, condensed milk, poured over ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry pinwheels
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Gradually stir in flour.
Shape dough into ball and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for several hours.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each portion into a 9 x 14-inch rectangle.

title: pink salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O evenly into cottage cheese.
Mix Cool Whip with Jell-O and cheese mixture until smooth.
Add fruit cocktail (well drained).
Mix gently until fruit is dispersed and keep in refrigerator until served.

title: beef ball
directions: Put dried beef and onion in food processor and chop well.
Mix in cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Form a ball or log.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger meat.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer until cooked well.
Pour over corn chips; top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and all is hot.

title: banana devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream shortening, 2 tablespoons buttermilk and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add banana pulp, then melted chocolate.
Combine remaining milk and vanilla; add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into oiled 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut pie(mary's new mexico)
directions: Place in saucepan
the
first
seven ingredients.
Over medium heat cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Lower heat and cook two minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir one cup hot mixture
into
slightly
beaten
yolks.
Return to heat.
Bring to a gentle boil and continue to cook two minutes more,
stirring constantly.
Remove
from
heat
and
stir
in butter and vanilla. Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle chopped chocolate covered peanuts on
top, while filling is still hot. If preferred you may want to
add a meringue top at this time. Cool completely, then store in refrigerator.

title: hoisin chicken
directions: Chop pepper coarsely.
Coat chicken pieces with 1/2 cup cornstarch.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Add chicken, 1 at a time, to hot oil (cook only 1/3 of pieces at a time).
Cook until golden and completely cooked (5 minutes).
Drain on paper when all pieces are cooked.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons oil from wok. Stir-fry ginger in oil over medium heat 1 minute.
Add onions to ginger; stir-fry over high heat 1 minute.
Add broccoli, pepper and mushrooms.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Combine water and all remaining ingredients and add to wok.
Cook and stir until warm and liquid boils.
Return chicken to wok and stir until chicken is hot, about 2 minutes.
Delicious!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour and eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) shallow pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole with lid.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
(You may put the crackers in melted butter if you like.)
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, without salt, until done.
Drain.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Make sauce by combining soup, milk, garlic salt, pimento and sharp cheese.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with Ritz crackers, rolled very fine.
Bake in a 350° oven until browned. Serves 8.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook until makes a soft ball, then add peanut butter.
After adding peanut butter make sure it makes a soft ball.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown the hamburg. Add all other ingredients. Put in baking pan. Slice 8 ounces cheese over it. Top with biscuits. Bake at 400°.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, beat egg, milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fill greased cupcake pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan. Serve hot with butter or margarine.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in casserole dish, saving one slice of cheese to garnish top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jezebel
directions: Prepare night before.
Mix jelly, preserves, horseradish, pepper and dry mustard together.
Drop cream cheese blocks into mixture.
Spoon one block of cream cheese onto cracker.
Top with mixture.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: best all-round punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add lemonade, almond extract and juice.
May freeze some in a ring or in plastic milk jugs to be used later.
Add 7-Up when serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Put next 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Set over low heat; bring gradually to the boiling point.
Boil 6 minutes.
Pour over chocolate.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat until the chocolate melts.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in lightly buttered pan about 8 x 12-inch.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except rhubarb.
Pour over the rhubarb in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes its own top crust.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix together.
Add onions and set aside.

title: southern-fried baked steak
directions: Pound steak to tenderize.
Cut into serving-sized pieces. Season with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.
Combine milk and egg; dip meat into egg mixture and back in flour.

title: 1-2-3 casserole
directions: Mix together after microwaving the broccoli to tenderize.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and add cheese on top.
Cook in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together and press in lightly greased (buttered) pan. Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips and spread over top.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Measure out peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Lightly butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix sugar and milk over high heat until mixture starts to boil.
Reduce to medium heat until soft ball stage.
Quickly add peanut butter and Fluff, stirring vigorously until blended.
Add vanilla.
Promptly pour into pan.

title: grandmother's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter, Crisco, cream cheese, and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour and vanilla last.
Grease and flour bundt pan or tube pan.
Put into cold oven.
Turn oven to 300 degrees and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before cutting.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Top each 1/2 chicken breast with cheese and ham, roll up and secure with skewers or toothpicks.
Melt butter in skillet and brown chicken 8 minutes, until nicely brown; remove from pan. Cook mushrooms and onions until tender.
Blend flour, gradually add milk and brandy or cooking sherry.
Stir constantly until thickened. (Nonstick pan only.)
Return chicken and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, every 2 minutes, for 20 minutes on low heat.
Meanwhile, cook noodles or rice of your choice. Serve chicken cut 1/2-inch thick slices.
Serve over noodles or rice and top with sauce.
Great company dish.

title: tomato dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl; mix until thoroughly blended.
Use the egg white, minced, to sprinkle over top of salad.
Makes about 2/3 of a cup dressing.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and margarine in skillet 10 minutes. Add broccoli; continue to saute.
Cook rice as directed.
When rice is done, add cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz to hot rice.
Add to vegetables.
Place in nongreased casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix and shape into 36 balls (1 teaspoon each).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
(Makes 15 large balls.) Serve with Dunky Sauce.

title: seasoned baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine browned beef with all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix together and cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites stiff and pour syrup into egg whites while hot.
Beat until stiff.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and nuts, if preferred.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions, peppers and hamburger until done. Add other ingredients. Mix well and simmer.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef
lightly
with
onion;
add tomatoes, tomato paste, water
and
seasonings.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Cook noodles. In a 13
x
9-inch
pan
put about 1 cup sauce, then alternate layers of
noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: appetizing shrimp
directions: Thaw and wash shrimp.
Melt butter and mix with Tabasco and shrimp.
Put in skillet, cover and cook for about 20 minutes without lifting cover.
Shake pan occasionally during cooking. Pour lemon juice over shrimp; stir well.
Drain all juices into bowl to use as a dip or sauce.

title: easy pickle recipe
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar,
salt
and celery seed until sugar is dissolved.	Let cool;
pour over pickles, onion and pepper. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Ready
to eat.
Do not freeze.
Keeps a month or so, covered.

title: fabulous flan(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put all ingredients except cinnamon in blender and blend well.

Pour mixture into baking dish or 4 individual ovenproof dishes and sprinkle generously with cinnamon. Place baking dish in preheated oven (if using small dishes, put on baking sheet) and bake 1 hour or until set.
May be served warm, at room temperature or cold.
Serves 4.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, tossing well with a fork.
Press into bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels, then butterscotch morsels over crust layer. Top with coconut, then with nuts.
Drizzle milk all over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: lemonade
directions: Remove seeds from lemons.
Quarter and process with ice and sugar.
(Use all of the lemon, peel included.)
Store in freezer in ice cube tray or other container.
When you need lemonade pour enough water over lemon-ice mixture to make 2 quarts (half gallon).
Viola!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat in oil. Remove. Cook onion in drippings. Add mushrooms and cook. Blend flour with 1/4 cup broth and add to pan. Add beef broth gradually, stirring constantly. Add salt, pepper, dill weed and dill seed.
Place ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Add sour cream just before serving over noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and fat.
Bake in hot oven.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add onion.
Heat vinegar, oil, salt and sugar. Mix; pour over beans and onion and let marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy, then beat in eggs. Add flour mixture and chill 1 hour. Cut out with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix pudding with Tang.
Dissolve with pineapple juice.
Mix until smooth and thick.
Add apples, oranges and pineapple. Chill.
Stir in 3 bananas when ready to serve.

title: sloppy onion burgers
directions: Brown
ground beef.
Add onion soup and simmer; thicken with flour.
Place
on buns and top with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: easy mexican pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chili with a little water to make it spreadable.
Pour chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread chili over top with cheese and onions.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.

title: favorite chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and peppers.
Put tomatoes in blender to liquify.
Add ingredients in large pot.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 3 hours.
Goes well with hush puppies and tossed salad.

title: grandma flossie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine the shortening, sugars, vanilla and water; beat until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chase's kahlua cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except Kahlua.
Beat 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in floured tube or Bundt pan.
When done, pour 1/4 cup Kahlua over cake.

title: cherry mash balls
directions: Work the first 4 ingredients together and shape into balls. Place them on waxed paper and freeze.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips, Spanish peanuts (run through blender) and paraffin.
Dip the cherry balls in chocolate and put on waxed paper.

title: goolacky
directions: Melt butter and sugar in heavy saucepan (won't be dissolved). Let cool some, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Bake in a 12 x 16-inch pan or 2 smaller ones. Cool and cut.

title: turkey and fixin's
directions: Cook turkey breast as directed.
Remove meat from bones in bite size pieces.
Combine soups and milk.
Pour over turkey pieces placed in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Prepare stuffing mix, adding celery and onion to boil with seasoning packet.
Spread over turkey.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a great holiday casserole for the buffet table.
Turkey, stuffing and gravy all in one!

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix the cake mix (dry), 1/3 cup evaporated milk, butter and nuts.
Press half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour over top a prepared mixture of melted caramels and the remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Sprinkle with remaining dough mixture and bake an additional 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Heat oil in frying pan. Saute chicken until golden brown.
Add onion, celery, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Continue to saute until tender. Add mushrooms, tomato sauce and red wine.
Cook for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serves with rice or noodles.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cut margarine into Bisquick; add milk.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured board.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick rectangle.
Mix sausage and spread on rectangle.
At this point, you can put grated cheese.
Roll jelly roll fashion; wrap in waxed paper, then foil. Keep frozen.
When ready to use, slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Good for brunch.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Beat egg yolks, add a small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks, beating well.
Stir egg mixture into hot mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Spoon into pie shell.
Beat egg whites, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar; continue beating until stiff.
Spread meringue over pie, sprinkle remaining coconut over top.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a 2-quart baking dish.
Stir in milk and vanilla making a thin batter.
Place fruit over the batter.
Do not stir.
Dot butter on top of fruit. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: In large frying pan, put potatoes and onions; pour water over them.
Salt and pepper.
You can add other herbs, if wished. Simmer potatoes, covered, for about 20 minutes or until soft and can cut into with fork.
Place cheese on top of potatoes and put cover back on.
Turn heat to low. Let cheese melt, takes only a few minutes.
Then they are ready to serve.

title: south main street cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend oats in blender until it becomes a fine powder.
Set aside.

Combine butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Stir in flour, salt and oatmeal. Toss in chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and pecans. Drop onto lightly buttered cookie sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking soda, cinnamon and nuts, a little at a time.
Add vanilla and apples to batter.
Mix and pour into a floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
at
350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top
of
cake
as
soon
as cake is taken out of oven (optional).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and blend together.
Add the cake flour, vanilla, lemon flavoring and the whipping cream, beating well.
Pour into a tube pan or Bundt pan.
Cook for one hour at 300°.

title: cold tea punch
directions: Steep tea.
Mix other ingredients.
Put in gallon container and finish filling with cold water.

title: gnocchi(makes 3 pounds)
directions: Mix the potatoes, boiling water and egg yolks.
Let rest awhile.
Mix with the butter; mix fast.
Add the flour, one cup at a time.
You will have a large ball of dough.
Cut pieces, then roll each piece into a rope.
Cut pieces about 3/4-inch long from the top.
With the index and middle finger, dig the pieces.
They will have an indentation in them.
Cook in boiling water until done.
They do not take long to cook.
Serve with spaghetti sauce and meatballs.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, milk, sugar, margarine, salt and 2 cups flour; stir well.
Let stand until it bubbles.
Add rest of flour; knead.
Let rise until double.
Work down, then make into rolls.
Let rise again in pan.
Cook at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes and beaten egg.
Add salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 round cakes about 3/4-inch thick.
Brown cakes on both sides in hot oil.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; gently shape into 1-inch balls. Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet; pour off fat.

title: rice and beef meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, salt, onion, oregano, rosemary and rice.
Shape the mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Heat the oil in a heavy 12-inch skillet over moderately low heat for about 1 minute.
Cut the meatballs, uncovered, turning frequently until browned on all sides (about 5 minutes).
Add the tomato sauce and water; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with a green salad and crusty Italian bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken supreme ala izzy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add mayonnaise and pimento; salt and pepper to taste.
Butter casserole. Dice 2 slices of bread.
Pat in bottom of casserole. Add chicken and mayonnaise mixture.
Dice other 4 slices of bread and pat on top. Mix eggs and milk together.
Pour over top of bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Spread soup and cheese mixture over the top of the casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix well the oatmeal, brown sugar, butter, flour and soda. Put aside 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, forming crust. Bake 10 to 15 minutes. In a saucepan, heat egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch, sour cream and raisins.
Cook over low heat.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into cooled crust.
Top with reserved crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and beat until smooth and fluffy. Add cream cheese; blend in eggs, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Stir slowly into cream cheese mixture.
Then add nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and cook over low heat until well blended, but not browned.
Gradually add 2 cups hot chicken stock, warm milk and cream, blending well.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until thick.
Add remaining 4 cups stock and diced chicken.
Heat to boiling.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve garnished with almonds.
Serves 10.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine milk, pudding and Amaretto.
Beat well with mixer until thick.
Blend in Cool Whip by hand until smooth.
Let sit overnight.
Serve with favorite fresh fruit.
Makes large quantity; can be cut in half.

title: spicy black beans(quick and easy)
directions: Drain a can of black beans and a can of whole kernel corn. Combine.
Add onion.
Pour salsa over all.
Let set overnight to mingle the flavors.
Good for picnics.

title: traditional gingerbread men
directions: Put shortening, sugar, spices and egg in a large mixer bowl. Mix until well blended.
Add molasses and mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Stir into shortening mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours for easier handling. Roll out on floured board and cut gingerbread men shapes.
Use bits of raisin for eyes, nose and buttons.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar, if desired.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about a dozen 5-inch gingerbread men.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat drippings in skillet; add remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, over low heat.
Stir occasionally.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: *The amount depends on how much you like each vegetable.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles. Cool, drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place a little sauce, then noodles in baking dish.
Half of cottage cheese mixture, then half of Mozzarella cheese, sauce again, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
If cold or frozen, bake 1 hour.

title: one bowl pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; beat at medium speed.
Grease tube pan with sugar and butter.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: oleta houston's pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender. Dip into cold water.
Peel off skins.
Make the syrup.
Pour the above syrup mixture over the beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: pork roast with spiced apples
directions: See Spiced Apples recipe.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Alternate layers of stuffing and chicken (save some stuffing for top).
Mix soups with 2 cans saved broth.
Pour over mixture.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: turkey-broccoli casserole
directions: Spoon stuffing into bottom of oiled shallow casserole.
Top with cubed turkey.
Add bouillon cubes to hot water and heat to boiling.
Blend flour into cold water and stir into hot liquid. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

Add broccoli and sour cream and pour mixture over turkey in casserole. Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes; top with triangles of sliced cheese and return to oven for 5 to 6 minutes until cheese begins to melt.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar until smooth.
Form balls the size of buckeyes.
Refrigerate balls.
Slowly melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Dip to about 2/3 covered.
Let dry on waxed paper.
Can be frozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cranberry sauce and stir to dissolve.
Add drained pineapple, put in a shallow dish about 1 inch deep; sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill overnight or several hours before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, peanut butter and honey.
Gradually add flour mixture and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood in a pot
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
rice cooker and season to taste. Cook until cooker goes off.

title: stuffed cabbage bundles
directions: Boil cabbage until leaves are wilted; separate leaves.
Mix all other ingredients and mold into egg-size balls.
Place each on a cabbage leaf, wrap and fasten with toothpicks.
Brown lightly in a greased skillet.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add a small amount of water if necessary.
You may serve with with tomato sauce or plain.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: taco dip
directions: Whip together sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Spread on serving dish.
Top with salsa, vegetables and cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put
altogether
in a 9 x 13-inch pan and mix.	Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rich custard
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils. Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in a little over half of this mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Blend into mixture in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix and roll into 2 oblong rolls.
Spread pan sausage (room temperature) over the dough. Roll and refrigerate or freeze. Remove from refrigerator
and slice.
Bake about 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together, then drain.
Mix meat mixture with sauce.
Alternate layers of meat sauce and noodles.
Bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Place cheese over top of casserole. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: english muffin crabmeat canape
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread English muffins with mixture.
Freeze slightly to cut.
Cut each half into 8 or more pie pieces.
Put in plastic bag and freeze.
When serving, place on broiler pan and cook a few minutes until cheese is light brown and melted.

title: do drop by dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour fruit into an ungreased 8 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over fruit.
Dot with the margarine.
Bake until golden (30 to 40 minutes).
Serve warm.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together all ingredients except peppers.
Slice stem end from peppers.
Remove seeds.
Stuff mixture in peppers.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour tomatoes or large can of sauce over peppers. Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: mom's spiced tea
directions: Bring 3 quarts water to boil.
Add tea bags and sugar.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Stir well and add cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices and serve hot.
Refrigerate between servings.

title: fluffy ambrosia
directions: Combine fruit cocktail, bananas, orange sections, nuts and marshmallows.
Fold fruit mixture into whipped cream.
Chill about an hour.
Spoon into dishes.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix well.
Place in buttered ring mold and bake in pan of water about 45 minutes at 350°.
Fill center of mold with English peas and serve.

title: colcannon
directions: Boil, drain and mash potatoes.
While potatoes are cooking, chop scallions and place in small bowl.
Pour boiling water over scallions to keep the tops green.
Bring milk almost to a boil; add drained scallions and pour over mashed potatoes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add egg and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour raw rice evenly in pan. Place chicken on top.
Blend soup and orange juice.
Pour over rice and chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with vegetable and salad.

title: lemon cheese squares
directions: Arrange 1/2 of the crackers in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, cutting crackers to fit. Beat cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed until smooth. Gradually beat in 1 cup of the milk. Add remaining milk and pudding mixes. Beat 1 to 2 minutes. Gently stir in 2 cups of the whipped topping. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture over crackers. Add second layer of crackers. Top with remaining pudding mixture and whipped topping. Freeze 2 hours or until firm. Garnish with pie filling. Store leftovers in freezer. Makes 18 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: vegetable rotini(serves 14)
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add vegetables for the last 5 minutes.
Drain.
In same pan over low heat, gradually stir soup into softened cream cheese; add milk, Parmesan cheese, mustard and pepper.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring often.
Add macaroni and vegetables; toss to coat.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into meatballs, 1 1/2 to 2-inch diameter.
Heat margarine and oil in large skillet.
Fry meatballs over low heat until brown and cooked through.
Great in spaghetti sauce.
Recipe can be doubled and half of meatballs frozen for future use.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt wax, add peanuts, syrup and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until candy turns golden brown.
Add salt and baking soda, stirring in fast.
Pour on 4 buttered plates.
Yields approximately 10 servings.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Saute the onion and chopped meat in butter.
Add pizza sauce and spices.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and spoon cheese mixture on top.
Cover and allow to melt.
Toast Italian bread under broiler.
Cube and dip in meat mixture.

title: pineapple cream cheese spread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes about 2 cups.
Form into ball or log.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain in cold water.
Bake chicken and put lemon pepper on it.
Dice chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook vegetables until crunchy, not soft.
Dice the garlic cloves real tiny and cut onion real fine.
Mix all together. Add pepper, parsley and shredded cheese.
Put dressing on, more or less according to taste.

title: chilled persian yogurt soup
directions: Beat the yogurt in an electric mixer or with a rotary beater. Combine the yogurt, cucumber, raisins and garlic with one cup of cold water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate for at least one hour.
When ready to serve, add the walnuts and dill to the soup.
Yields 8 servings.
